INSERT INTO `journal_entries` VALUES (4,'Tuesday','Today was much easier than the last. I was beyond tired on Monday as I made the crucial error of sleeping at 12:30 KNOWING I would have to wake up at 5:30am. \n\nToday was a regular day of some ups and downs. I had a small fight with Tais. It doesn\'t matter what it was. We made up quickly as always. \n\nI enjoyed spending time with Noah. He is growing up so fast, and although the days can be long (or too fast rather), every minute with him is counted as a blessing. \n\nFor the past few weeks I have been faced with doubt about whether its worth studying CS. However, time and time again I come to the same conclusion. IT IS! The future holds many possible paths. \n\nI am enjoying the C Programming book, and my productivity suite (ai drive php app builder) is doing fantastic. This marks the first day of the journal app coming to life! ','happy','2026-01-13','2026-01-14 03:50:28','2026-01-14 03:55:57'),(10,'No more Gaming','Just got rid of my gaming laptop for good. Now I am using a Dell laptop with working people specs. I love it and hate it at the same time. Will now buy a ton of systems engineering gear, and we\'re off to the races.','neutral','2026-01-24','2026-01-25 00:25:52','2026-01-25 00:26:43'),(12,'I ordered a Zenbook','I ordered a new laptop. The Asus Zenbook 14. Its got all the bells and whistles but it turns out its probably overkill for what I need. Instead I\'m going to spend half the amount of money on a Thinkpad P1 Gen 3 (without the Nvidia GPU). Should be pretty good! Wallmart messed up the delivery so I feel like this is a sign from God. Also I\'m sick and wasting time on this stupid home-server app. \n','happy','2026-02-04','2026-02-04 20:08:05','2026-02-04 20:13:28'),(13,'Another one','Another day of being at home sick. 3 days going strong. Feeling better. Thanking God for all the blessings that we receive and completely take for granted. Spent some time with baby Noah, watched an episode of Physical Asia. Can’t complain. New Dell bought on Ebay on the way. \n\nLearned all about manipulation and low level programming. ','happy','2026-02-06','2026-02-07 04:14:52','2026-02-07 04:17:20'),(14,'AI Thought - Compromise','It has occurred to me that AI’s limitation seems to have less to do with its ability to memorize, but rather its lack of ability to selectively forget. \n\nIn the pursuit of a major goal, limitations and real world constraints produce shifts in that goal. The goal itself may change, which makes previous steps irrelevant. It is navigating this nature of problem solving that AI seems to have trouble with - it has poor ability to compromise, and instead seeks to implement the originally stated goal at all costs, no matter how ridiculous.\n\nHowever, it is proving quite sufficient as a code monkey - which is great! ','happy','2026-02-20','2026-02-20 19:14:09','2026-03-08 03:16:45'),(17,'AI is starting to get really fun... And my son is awesome','I have been collecting really impressive SKILL.md collections which have been written by pros in their field. Never has been vibe coding been so easy. Right now its personal web apps (easy breezy). Can\'t wait to see what people whip up in terms of scalable software applications etc., \n\nI have spent many hours today implementing an auto newsletter and a discord bot named Jarvis instead of reading the Book of Proof which is what I should have been doing. \nTHIS is why AI is bad for your brain.\n\nBaby Noah is starting to be super responsive. Clapping his hands, waving. Absolutely priceless. They grow up so fast, and every moment is to be treasured, because it will all feel like it went away much too quickly. If you\'re reading this someday Noah, I love you with all my heart and soul.','great','2026-03-13','2026-03-14 03:33:37','2026-03-14 03:38:23'),(19,'Quote of the day','If what you want to do is always colliding with what you think is worth doing, you will never do anything for long enough to be a master at it.\n\nYou must always believe that it is worth doing the things you love.\n\n- me','great','2026-05-18','2026-05-19 03:15:52','2026-05-19 03:18:13');
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `journal_entries` ENABLE KEYS */;
UNLOCK TABLES;

