INSERT INTO `newsletters` VALUES (3,'Daily Planet - March 14, 2026','Sir,\n\nA new day dawns with a complex tapestry of global events, dominated by escalating geopolitical tensions and rapid advancements in artificial intelligence, alongside their nascent challenges.\n\n### **Global Flashpoints & Geopolitical Maneuvers**\n\nThe Middle East finds itself once again at the precipice of significant escalation, with reports indicating a substantial increase in US military presence, including Marines and warships, in the region. This comes amidst a series of volatile incidents: the US Embassy in Baghdad suffered a missile strike to its helipad, and US officials, including former President Trump, have blamed Iran for military actions, including alleged \"obliteration\" of targets on Kharg Island and a school strike. The looming economic threat of such a conflict, particularly rising food prices, is now a significant concern. Further south, an airstrike in Lebanon tragically claimed the lives of the family of a suspect in a Michigan synagogue attack, highlighting the interconnectedness of regional conflicts. Simultaneously, exiled Kurdish groups in the region face drone fire as they anticipate confrontations with the Iranian regime, while reports from Al Jazeera allege that Israel is systematically targeting civilian infrastructure.\n\nElsewhere on the global stage, North Korea demonstrated its continued defiance by firing ballistic missiles during joint military drills conducted by the US and South Korea, underscoring persistent regional instability. Domestically, a serious anti-monopoly case against Live Nation is moving forward in states\' courts, and allegations linking the chief of the LA28 Olympics to Jeffrey Epstein\'s network have prompted an official investigation. A harrowing report from South Africa has also shed light on the dire conditions of gold miners, with accusations of deliberate starvation.\n\n### **The AI Frontier & Technological Shifts**\n\nThe realm of artificial intelligence continues its relentless march forward, yet with a distinct sense of both groundbreaking achievement and emergent growing pains. Anthropic has made its 1M context window generally available for Opus 4.6 and Sonnet 4.6, marking a significant leap in large language model capabilities. However, the path to innovation remains fraught, as evidenced by Elon Musk\'s xAI reportedly \'starting over again, again,\' a testament to the immense complexities of building advanced AI.\n\nConcerns around AI\'s darker implications are also intensifying: a lawyer involved in AI psychosis cases has issued a stark warning about potential mass casualty risks. This underscores the critical need for human oversight and context, a gap that Nyne, a new venture by a father-son duo, aims to fill by imbuing AI agents with crucial human understanding. Meanwhile, AI is increasingly permeating consumer electronics, with Microsoft\'s Copilot assistant slated for integration into current-gen Xbox consoles this year. The disruptive nature of AI is also becoming apparent in platform dynamics; the once-prominent social news aggregator Digg has shut down its app and laid off staff, citing an inability to combat AI bot spam in its open beta. This era is also prompting traditional tools to adapt, with discussions emerging on the future of editors like Emacs and Vim in an AI-powered world.\n\nOn the critical hardware front, a sudden helium shutdown in Qatar has put the global chip supply chain on a precarious two-week clock, highlighting a significant vulnerability in the foundation of modern technology. Social media platforms are also responding to evolving challenges, with Facebook introducing new tools to help creators report impersonators, a likely response to the rise of sophisticated deepfakes.\n\n### **Quick Hits**\n\n*   **Political Economy:** Subpoenas against Fed chair Jerome Powell have been dismissed in a scathing opinion, closing a chapter on legal challenges to the central bank\'s leadership.\n*   **Telecom Landscape:** The US mobile carrier market sees the rise of ideologically-aligned options, with \"Trump Mobile\" joining a growing crowd of conservative-leaning providers like Radiant, Patriot, PureTalk, and Charity Liberty.\n*   **Alpine Tragedies:** Rescuers are attributing a rise in Alps avalanche deaths to severe weather conditions and the \'underprepared\' nature of many skiers, urging greater caution.\n*   **Self-Improvement:** A thought-provoking 2016 essay by Andrej Karpathy, \"A Survival Guide to a PhD,\" continues to resonate as a valuable resource for navigating rigorous academic pursuits.\n*   **Digital Personalization:** Spotify is reportedly testing features allowing users to directly customize their \'Taste Profile,\' offering more granular control over algorithmic recommendations.','[{\"title\": \"1M context is now generally available for Opus 4.6 and Sonnet 4.6\", \"url\": \"https://claude.com/blog/1m-context-ga\"}, {\"title\": \"A Survival Guide to a PhD (2016)\", \"url\": \"http://karpathy.github.io/2016/09/07/phd/\"}, {\"title\": \"Emacs and Vim in the Age of AI\", \"url\": \"https://batsov.com/articles/2026/03/09/emacs-and-vim-in-the-age-of-ai/\"}, {\"title\": \"You gotta think outside the hypercube\", \"url\": \"https://lcamtuf.substack.com/p/you-gotta-think-outside-the-hypercube\"}, {\"title\": \"Qatar helium shutdown puts chip supply chain on a two-week clock\", \"url\": \"https://www.tomshardware.com/tech-industry/qatar-helium-shutdown-puts-chip-supply-chain-on-a-two-week-clock\"}, {\"title\": \"\\u2018Not built right the first time\\u2019 \\u2014 Musk\\u2019s xAI is starting over again, again\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/13/not-built-right-the-first-time-musks-xai-is-starting-over-again-again/\"}, {\"title\": \"Lawyer behind AI psychosis cases warns of mass casualty risks\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/13/lawyer-behind-ai-psychosis-cases-warns-of-mass-casualty-risks/\"}, {\"title\": \"Digg lays off staff and shuts down app as company retools\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/13/digg-lays-off-staff-and-shuts-down-app-as-company-retools/\"}, {\"title\": \"Nyne, founded by a father-son duo, gives AI agents the human context they\\u2019re missing\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/13/nyne-founded-by-a-father-son-duo-gives-ai-agents-the-human-context-theyre-missing/\"}, {\"title\": \"Facebook makes it easier for creators to report impersonators\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/13/facebook-makes-it-easier-for-creators-to-report-impersonators/\"}, {\"title\": \"States\\u2019 anti-monopoly case against Live Nation continues Monday\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/policy/894851/states-live-nation-monopoly-trial\"}, {\"title\": \"Spotify tests letting users directly customize their Taste Profile\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/entertainment/894753/spotify-taste-profile\"}, {\"title\": \"Microsoft\\u2019s Copilot AI assistant is coming to current-gen Xbox consoles this year\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/games/894799/microsoft-gaming-copilot-ai-xbox-consoles\"}, {\"title\": \"Trump Mobile is just one in the crowd of conservative carriers\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/894762/trump-mobile-conservative-mvno-radiant-patriot-puretalk-charity-liberty\"}, {\"title\": \"Digg\\u2019s open beta shuts down after just two months, blaming AI bot spam\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/894803/digg-beta-shutdown-layoffs-ai\"}, {\"title\": \"Vivid Seats Promo Codes and Deals: Save 10% This March\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/vivid-seats-promo-code/\"}, {\"title\": \"Coleman Promo Codes and Deals: Up to 30% Off in March\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/coleman-promo-code/\"}, {\"title\": \"Chirp Discount Codes and Deals: Save Up to 67%\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/chirp-discount-code/\"}, {\"title\": \"What to Do in Vegas If You\\u2019re Here for Business (2026)\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/in-transit-las-vegas/\"}, {\"title\": \"Best Dreo Spring Sale Deals: Air Fryer, Heater, Fans\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/dreo-spring-sale-deals-dreo-chefmaker/\"}, {\"title\": \"More US Marines and warships to be moved to Middle East, reports say\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cq8gj9n12g8o?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Rescuers blame weather and \'underprepared skiers\' for rise in Alps avalanche deaths\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cev7111kx9wo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Los Angeles asks for investigation into LA28 Olympics chief over Epstein ties\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cn9ewxq98e5o?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Under drone fire, exiled Kurds wait to confront Iranian regime\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c79505804lpo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Family of Michigan synagogue suspect killed in Lebanon airstrike, officials say\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cdxz0jpzk4do?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Indian-owned Sunrisers face backlash after signing Pakistan\\u2019s Abrar Ahmed\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2026/3/14/indian-owned-sunrisers-face-backlash-after-signing-pakistans-abrar-ahmed?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"\\u2018Kill the people\\u2019: How men were left to starve in a South African gold mine\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/features/longform/2026/3/14/kill-the-people-how-men-were-left-to-starve-in-a-south-african-gold-mine?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"North Korea fires ballistic missiles as US-South Korea hold military drills\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/3/14/north-korea-fires-ballistic-missiles-as-us-south-korea-hold-military-drills?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"\\u2018Israel is targeting civilian infrastructure as a matter of policy\\u2019\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/video/quotable/2026/3/14/israel-is-targeting-civilian-infrastructure-as-a-matter-of-policy?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"US Embassy in Baghdad, Iraq attacked with missile that hits helipad\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/3/14/us-embassy-in-baghdad-iraq-targeted-with-missile-hits-helipad?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Iran War News Live Updates: Trump Says U.S. Bombs \\u2018Obliterated\\u2019 Military Targets on Kharg Island - WSJ\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMibkFVX3lxTE9yMkxEQUxCd19ONlZmSTFMQUNtOHhoeDdKZ2ZiN2MwcUhyM2IycWxrbHVkTUZLY2FBSXRHZ0RLLTZMaVduRHVFMUhlQndHQm1ENWZVb1FfLUhCcWJOQldmdlRkTmhSZTNZak9FeGJn?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Subpoenas against Fed chair Powell tossed in a scathing opinion - Axios\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMiZkFVX3lxTFBaS1dTa3hBMS05aG1ZalBEeHdPU3p6ZXM2bDB0ekIyb0NzYVZOVzRHT0dKN2NWeWFhSkp5TUp5Y0I2NFAtRmM4V1IzLXhsRldDUk5oOU9vQ3dZOFBRMm84MVpqQ3dGUQ?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"The Iran war\'s looming economic threat: Higher food prices - NBC News\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMijAFBVV95cUxNbmFLc3FkeGRvSm85ZlFjbnNVWVYwbVRWYnRDdVJuNEZUYTdScjhHTkxrSVpsTmFtWVFDVTJzaWRwN2l5ekZNbm9tYWtidHJ3N2VLUTc2VGlIY2hmOG5zUEVFU3RVbElQUy16S0NHNjVjcm0tZmpzS2hiZW1rRzB5cHRGX0NCNUZ4VWhKRg?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Hegseth vows thorough probe of school strike that Trump blamed on Iran - The Washington Post\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMikAFBVV95cUxOeXVEaEZjNzB3dmVzRjJSR2hXQXh2cUtIbEJ4RkUwaHJ5el9LMjVvVUxZYlZiWVpXM0FfZGlaZS14VVRobFp0WVg3ZEhpV2ZjdWJ5UDZwRGt3NkFQT2ZUR1g0OHZlMXRYZUp2QWRFMTBBWmR3S1BTV3h0WS11SGtMM05hbURRc1ZsNE4yeUpGMkE?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Temple Israel Staff Raced to Save Lives in Michigan Synagogue Attack - The New York Times - The New York Times\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMiiAFBVV95cUxOVG1TamQ2eWNReWNfMVJqdmNtTGF3cWVkR2txTVl1RXQyTlMtdm52bXJHMTdjTWU1elJfRWdnMWtrdVJSUUhhZDd4eEtpUVRwV2FwOUhPTUNMQzNkVVdkbk1fTVBvNU9rSGFiUENCVVNOZlNwWk1vLTg5cVo1eTh3WVk3aGRyZ3lQ?oc=5\"}]','2026-03-14 09:00:43'),(4,'Daily Planet - March 15, 2026','## The Daily Planet – March 15, 2026\n\n**Geopolitical Instability & Conflict Escalation**\n\nThe international landscape remains deeply concerning. Tensions in the Middle East have reached a critical juncture, with escalating conflict impacting regional stability and drawing in external actors. Reports indicate an Israeli strike in Lebanon resulting in civilian casualties, alongside continued IDF targeting of Hezbollah. Simultaneously, former President Trump has called for international naval intervention in the Strait of Hormuz, a move that, coupled with reports of an attack on the U.S. Embassy in Baghdad, underscores a rapidly deteriorating security situation. Al Jazeera reports rallies both protesting and supporting action against Iran, highlighting the deeply divided opinions surrounding the crisis. Disturbingly, reports from Al Jazeera also detail a strike in Minab, Iran, allegedly utilizing a highly precise missile against a classroom – the veracity of which requires independent verification, but demands immediate attention. The FCC is also reportedly considering revoking licenses from broadcasters deemed to be covering the conflict inadequately, raising concerns about freedom of the press.  Further unrest is brewing in Cuba, with protesters ransacking a Communist Party office amidst widespread energy blackouts, signaling potential for broader political upheaval. \n\n**Tech Sector Turbulence & Innovation**\n\nThe technology sector presents a mixed picture of innovation and potential contraction. Meta is reportedly considering layoffs affecting up to 20% of its workforce – a significant restructuring that signals concerns about future growth and profitability. This follows a pattern of belt-tightening across the tech industry. In contrast, Apple’s new MacBook Neo is receiving praise from iFixit for its unprecedented repairability, a welcome shift towards more sustainable and consumer-friendly hardware design. However, Honda has made the drastic decision to halt its EV development, a move that analysts suggest could severely hamper its future competitiveness in the automotive market. \n\nOn the defense front, Anduril has secured a potentially massive contract with the U.S. Army, valued at up to $20 billion, indicating a continued investment in advanced defense technologies.  Meanwhile, innovation continues at a granular level: researchers have published a remarkably elegant algorithm for TCP hole punching, a critical technique for establishing direct connections through network address translation (NAT).  Security remains a paramount concern, with detailed analyses emerging on how kernel-level anti-cheat systems function, and a sobering report detailing how a hacker accidentally gained access to the FBI’s sensitive Epstein files.\n\n**Quick Hits**\n\n* **Treasure & the Law:** A treasure hunter has been released from jail after refusing to disclose the location of shipwreck gold, raising complex legal questions about salvage rights and maritime law.\n* **Mathematical Curiosities:** A fascinating deep dive explores why Mathematica struggles to simplify the expression sinh(arccosh(x)), highlighting the nuances of symbolic computation.\n* **Refurbished Electronics:** WIRED offers a comprehensive guide to purchasing used or refurbished electronics, a smart strategy for cost-conscious consumers.\n* **Pi & Probability:** A surprisingly intuitive method for approximating Pi using dropped needles is gaining attention.\n* **Samsung Galaxy S26 Ultra:** Early reviews of the Samsung Galaxy S26 Ultra highlight its innovative privacy screen technology.\n* **Identity Theft Protection:** A critical assessment of the value proposition of identity theft protection services.\n* **Oscars & Prediction Markets:** Prediction markets are leveraging the Oscars as a gateway to broader betting on entertainment and current events.\n* **MacBook Air M5:** The latest MacBook Air M5 receives a lukewarm review, described as a minor update to an already solid product.\n* **TikTok Deal:** The Trump administration is allegedly seeking $10 billion in connection with a potential TikTok deal.\n* **Social Connection:** New apps are emerging aimed at facilitating new friendships, addressing a growing need for social connection in the digital age.\n* **MotoGP Postponement:** The Qatar Grand Prix has been postponed due to the ongoing conflict in the Middle East.\n\n\n\n','[{\"title\": \"Rack-mount hydroponics\", \"url\": \"https://sa.lj.am/rack-mount-hydroponics/\"}, {\"title\": \"Why Mathematica does not simplify sinh(arccosh(x))\", \"url\": \"https://www.johndcook.com/blog/2026/03/10/sinh-arccosh/\"}, {\"title\": \"Treasure hunter freed from jail after refusing to turn over shipwreck gold\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cg4g7kn99q3o\"}, {\"title\": \"A most elegant TCP hole punching algorithm\", \"url\": \"https://robertsdotpm.github.io/cryptography/tcp_hole_punching.html\"}, {\"title\": \"How kernel anti-cheats work\", \"url\": \"https://s4dbrd.github.io/posts/how-kernel-anti-cheats-work/\"}, {\"title\": \"The MacBook Neo is \\u2018the most repairable MacBook\\u2019 in years, according to iFixit\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/14/the-macbook-neo-is-the-most-repairable-macbook-in-years-according-to-ifixit/\"}, {\"title\": \"US Army announces contract with Anduril worth up to $20B\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/14/us-army-announces-contract-with-anduril-worth-up-to-20b/\"}, {\"title\": \"Honda is killing its EVs \\u2014\\u00a0and any chance of competing in the future\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/14/honda-is-killing-its-evs-and-any-chance-of-competing-in-the-future/\"}, {\"title\": \"Meta reportedly considering layoffs that could affect 20% of the company\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/14/meta-reportedly-considering-layoffs-that-could-affect-20-of-the-company/\"}, {\"title\": \"As people look for ways to make new friends, here are the apps promising to help\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/14/as-people-look-for-ways-to-make-new-friends-here-are-the-apps-promising-to-help/\"}, {\"title\": \"Trump administration is allegedly collecting $10 billion on the TikTok deal\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/policy/895039/trump-10-billion-tiktok\"}, {\"title\": \"Meta is reportedly laying off up to 20 percent of its staff\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/business/895026/meta-laying-off-20-percent\"}, {\"title\": \"Hulu, Disney Plus, and the Pixel Watch 4 are among this week\\u2019s best deals\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/gadgets/894699/hulu-disney-plus-subscription-oscars-google-pixel-watch-4-deal-sale\"}, {\"title\": \"Prediction markets want the Oscars to be your gateway drug to betting on everything\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/entertainment/894878/oscars-2026-kalshi-sinners-one-battle-after-anothers-marty-supreme-baftas-gambling\"}, {\"title\": \"MacBook Air M5 review: a small update for the \\u2018just right\\u2019 Mac\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/894866/apple-macbook-air-m5-15-2026-laptop-review\"}, {\"title\": \"How to Buy Used or Refurbished Electronics (2026)\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/how-to-buy-refurbished-electronics/\"}, {\"title\": \"You Can Approximate Pi by Dropping Needles on the Floor\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/you-can-approximate-pi-by-dropping-needles-on-the-floor/\"}, {\"title\": \"Samsung Galaxy S26 Ultra Review: The Privacy Screen\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/review/samsung-galaxy-s26-ultra/\"}, {\"title\": \"A Hacker Accidentally Broke Into the FBI\\u2019s Epstein Files\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/security-news-this-week-a-hacker-accidentally-broke-into-the-fbis-epstein-files/\"}, {\"title\": \"Identity Theft Protection Services: Do You Actually Need One?\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/best-id-protection-services/\"}, {\"title\": \"BBC visits aftermath of Israeli strike on Lebanon that killed family as IDF targets Hezbollah\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c20lvn0ex6yo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Trump urges UK and other nations to send warships to Strait of Hormuz\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cd039n9vj3vo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Three more Iran football team members change minds over asylum\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c98gz372683o?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"\'Gruesome\' war bets fuel calls for crackdown on prediction markets\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cjwz8051y0lo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Cuban protesters ransack Communist office as energy crisis deepens\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c875zd7de5xo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"MotoGP postpones Qatar Grand Prix due to Middle East conflict\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2026/3/15/motogp-postpones-qatar-grand-prix-due-to-middle-east-conflict?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Activists rally outside White House against war with Iran\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/video/newsfeed/2026/3/15/activists-rally-outside-white-house-against-war-with-iran?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Al-Quds Day rally in Toronto calls for an end to the war in Iran & Lebanon\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/video/newsfeed/2026/3/15/al-quds-day-rally-in-toronto-calls-for-an-end-to-the-war-in-iran-lebanon?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Minab: When the world\\u2019s most precise missile chose a classroom\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/opinions/2026/3/15/minab-when-the-worlds-most-precise-missile-chose-a-classroom?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Smoke rises over Beirut\\u2019s southern suburbs\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/video/newsfeed/2026/3/15/smoke-rises-over-beiruts-southern-suburbs?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Trump urges world to help open Strait of Hormuz; U.S. Embassy in Baghdad hit - The Washington Post\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMiwwFBVV95cUxQNVA5eFpYMThSQmVXYk1rMUxZWVU2REVGclphQXJqUzlyaDVrRTdaZ3BMQUYtOHZCOGFwTE9VZDVMWjQxdUlkbGNjS2YyTHhjT0hKOTcwT1psa0V2OWtoN1JOU1U1bVBGT1MyUWl1ZFlqRE9KQ2pDQ0VPMlI0bXA5cElqeEdtblZ1MlVybVpMbnVGWjJJWm5hTTJ1emtfWmh3b2dKNWF0RHROOGE0Q2NYSEFNT3EwTkRITUtRUWdMNDJkQ1k?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Covington Air Force Captain among six identified in Iraq refueling plane crash - KOMO\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"F.C.C. Chair Threatens to Revoke Broadcasters\\u2019 Licenses Over War Coverage - The New York Times\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMiigFBVV95cUxQWFhQSW53M2FvN0pnUGJ3YnIxMW9acWJIMWx6MDEwck1EMFo5MkJQY1J2dXNnZnlpZTRyV3JvWUhvOW1KWDFxbmZGTWFWUHhMSEFENzRFUDRBei1ULUo4OWM0a1FxRHk3Smc3OVVXMW9yR3VIVlBFa2lvUU1fcnNjSjZiWWRsVXh3MFE?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Middle East crisis live: Trump \\u2018surprised\\u2019 Iran has targeted Gulf countries and claims US \\u2018decimated\\u2019 Kharg Island - The Guardian\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMixAFBVV95cUxOZ1M3bUpvZzd5dENxOG1xTHdab2ZORWhrUGtZNVNJNDU5dGV5dk9VeUhzWmVYUFY5cUFlUk1MOXRmY0VBZE5nM3AyUDgxX3BKdDhEZUNORVl2cmRWZEpaY0lmeHRWbDcxZjFsbHcxV19IS2syRWtuaDNZbmxqRE5WX3FyclRSLXdKcXpoWGw4OUpKSWNQQ1FYUlNyVlhhaXVGZnlkRnZnNVByYmFhLWRjaFpQcE1pQ2xJMWxOOTE2a2VMQ01N?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Cuba: Protesters attack ruling party\'s office amid blackouts - dw.com\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.?oc=5\"}]','2026-03-15 09:01:09'),(7,'Daily Planet - March 16, 2026','### The Daily Planet\n\n#### Global Crisis: The Iran Conflict and Regional Instability\nThe seventeenth day of conflict in the Middle East has entered a precarious new phase. Following US-Israel strikes, Iran’s leadership faces internal and external turmoil; reports indicate that Mojtaba Khamenei has been secretly evacuated to Russia for surgery, while the Iranian Foreign Ministry has rebuffed any potential dialogue with the United States. The geopolitical strain is manifesting in the physical world: the closure of the Strait of Hormuz is already exerting upward pressure on global grocery prices, forcing Japan to tap its oil reserves to mitigate an escalating energy crisis. Meanwhile, drone strikes continue to disrupt transit, including flights in Dubai, and Tehran’s domestic stability remains in question as the regime attempts to stifle rising anti-establishment sentiment. Adding to the friction, Donald Trump has issued a stark warning to NATO allies, threatening a \"very bad\" future for the alliance should they fail to assist in securing the critical Strait.\n\n#### Tech & Innovation: The Evolving Landscape\nThe tech industry is currently navigating a period of both ethical reckoning and strategic consolidation. \n*   **The AI Pivot:** Investors are signaling a shift in priorities; a recent Google and Accel accelerator cohort in India notably excluded \"AI wrappers,\" favoring startups with more tangible, defensible utility. Simultaneously, legal and ethical concerns are mounting, with warnings of potential \"mass casualty\" risks tied to AI psychosis, while creative sectors are mobilizing against the mass harvesting of human emotional data, particularly from improv actors.\n*   **Engineering & Infrastructure:** In the developer ecosystem, Chrome DevTools has introduced MCP to streamline browser debugging, while ByteDance has hit the pause button on the global rollout of its Seedance 2.0 video generator. On the hardware front, the discourse is shifting toward fundamental limits—specifically the physics of electric motor scaling—while the vision for a decentralized web continues to evolve through projects like Aether OS, designed for the AT Protocol.\n\n#### Quick Hits\n*   **Surveillance Overreach:** Privacy advocates are sounding alarms over Canada’s Bill C-22, which risks codifying dangerous metadata surveillance and warrantless access.\n*   **Culture & Entertainment:** At the Oscars, Netflix’s *Frankenstein* dominated with three wins, followed by *KPop Demon Hunters*. In music, Sotomayor’s *Wabi Sabi* is being hailed as the standout record of 2026.\n*   **Climate Extremes:** The United States and Hawaii are currently grappling with severe, anomalous weather, ranging from dangerous blizzard conditions in Minnesota to flash flooding and landslides in Hawaii.\n*   **Consumer Pulse:** For those looking to capitalize on the 2026 Amazon Spring Sale, expert analysis suggests filtering the noise for select tech and wellness deals, while the Brompton Electric T-Line continues to redefine urban mobility for the premium commuter.\n*   **Global Unrest:** Beyond the Middle East, the Ugandan opposition leader has sought asylum abroad, citing fears for his safety, and US-based groups are increasingly influencing the trajectory of anti-abortion activism within the United Kingdom.','[{\"title\": \"Canada\'s bill C-22 mandates mass metadata surveillance\", \"url\": \"https://www.michaelgeist.ca/2026/03/a-tale-of-two-bills-lawful-access-returns-with-changes-to-warrantless-access-but-dangerous-backdoor-surveillance-risks-remains/\"}, {\"title\": \"The 49MB web page\", \"url\": \"https://thatshubham.com/blog/news-audit\"}, {\"title\": \"How I write software with LLMs\", \"url\": \"https://www.stavros.io/posts/how-i-write-software-with-llms/\"}, {\"title\": \"Chrome DevTools MCP (2025)\", \"url\": \"https://developer.chrome.com/blog/chrome-devtools-mcp-debug-your-browser-session\"}, {\"title\": \"Electric motor scaling laws and inertia in robot actuators\", \"url\": \"https://robot-daycare.com/posts/actuation_series_1/\"}, {\"title\": \"The billionaires made a promise \\u2014 now some want out\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/15/the-billionaires-made-a-promise-now-some-want-out/\"}, {\"ti