 strike disrupts Dubai flights as Iran continues Gulf attacks\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/3/16/drone-strike-disrupts-dubai-flights-as-iran-continues-gulf-attacks?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"\\u2018Stop all these wars now\\u2019 says Oscar winner\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/video/newsfeed/2026/3/16/stop-all-these-wars-now-says-oscar-winner?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Japan begins release of oil reserves as Iran war sparks energy crisis\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/economy/2026/3/16/japan-begins-release-of-oil-reserves-as-iran-war-sparks-energy-crisis?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Middle East crisis live: Trump threatens \\u2018very bad\\u2019 future for Nato if allies fail to help secure strait of Hormuz - The Guardian\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMiwAFBVV95cUxPWG1qOXZBa2Q1R2NrQ19TenBuYVF0Q1pmZjQ3emROTmNiNnVodkdFTENOWEVoeUp5X25jWXJIVFU1XzdSLVUwazhmQ0lmZy12MHlseEVsX1lBZFpubFctOHNaaHBJc1B4dm5kbkk5Yjc2T0VEX3FLQXFIbWtsZ3NNRVR4TmUzVDRzem1oZzAxUkE5Um1VNGszNUdwSS1wVzRJeENwXzZvUkVaR2VhN1VCUDJhYTRUVldwa0Myb0dKVkE?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"\'Lost one leg\': Iran\'s new leader Mojtaba Khamenei secretly flown to Russia for surgery, says report - WION\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Iranian foreign minister says \\\"we don\'t see any reason why we should talk with Americans\\\" - CBS News\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Authorities advise no travel across southern Minnesota as blizzard conditions continue - MPR News\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMitgFBVV95cUxNZGp4TVlxb21JX09HNzNHa2huNThHRVR3MUtCMDBLd0phZFFWVGowUER6T1JpSnhyYkRKSXhOWlk2YmJPcURJRVBiVG9Zb01sMzM3YnUydHctRWZINm1oUEo3dVhGdmU0X21uTkx5eGR6SVFpSWQ4ZmJPNW5PckJFaEZnUlZySTNWaDBGaDRwcGJiclJRRGZ6SEF1SHJHYUpRcGRrUzl1RG91djhRTEdDV1RSX3ZBZw?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Hawaii faces flash flooding, blizzard conditions and landslides with more rain to come - The Guardian\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMiekFVX3lxTE0zZDg5UVRyY3BnbVJnZUpORG15T3RqSTZ3NDlVTnpoQ0sxNllsOHFCcXRIWG9Cc2dmcGxIeDJ1bEs4X0l0RDVsc1pxbFNtNklEd0dGTUxQMm01Yjl5SlZmTTRuRkl4RGxoX2ZTQkxpZEFLOE5WdVhuX2pB?oc=5\"}]','2026-03-16 09:00:45'),(12,'Daily Planet - March 17, 2026','### Global Affairs: Geopolitics and Conflict\nThe international stage is marked by heightened volatility as military strikes and diplomatic realignments command attention. In the Middle East, escalating tensions between Iran and the U.S. have prompted Iranian forces to target shipping vessels, drawing responses from Washington and further straining regional stability. Amidst this, Donald Trump has opted to delay his scheduled meeting with President Xi Jinping in China, citing the complexity of the brewing Iran conflict. Elsewhere, regional violence continues to claim civilian lives; a deadly strike on a rehabilitation center in Kabul has left families searching for loved ones, while in Lebanon, ongoing Israeli bombardments are forcing a fresh wave of displacement for Palestinian refugees.\n\nIn domestic news, the political discourse remains sharp: Donald Trump has faced significant backlash for disparaging comments regarding Governor Gavin Newsom’s dyslexia, while the administration’s health policy faced a setback as a federal judge halted Robert F. Kennedy Jr.’s vaccine overhaul initiative, citing procedural flaws. On a lighter but significant diplomatic note, Nigerian President Bola Tinubu has departed for the UK, marking the first Nigerian state visit to the country since 1989. Meanwhile, a high-profile legal case in Utah concluded with the conviction of a bereavement author for the poisoning of her husband.\n\n### Tech and Innovation: AI, Infrastructure, and Security\nThe tech sector is grappling with the rapid integration of artificial intelligence and the scrutiny that follows. Nvidia continues its meteoric rise, with Jensen Huang projecting astronomical sales for the Blackwell and Vera Rubin architectures; concurrently, the company is seeking to address long-standing security concerns through an expansion of its OpenClaw platform and the introduction of DLSS 5, which functions effectively as a real-time generative AI filter for gaming.\n\nHowever, the rapid deployment of these tools is not without controversy. Teens have filed a lawsuit against Elon Musk’s xAI, alleging that the Grok assistant generated child sexual abuse material (CSAM). Furthermore, Senator Elizabeth Warren has intensified pressure on the Pentagon regarding its decision to grant xAI access to sensitive classified networks. \n\nBeyond AI, the infrastructure of the digital world is seeing foundational shifts. Meta has renewed its commitment to *jemalloc* for data infrastructure, while the open-source community gains a powerful tool with the release of *Leanstral*, an agent designed for secure coding and formal proof engineering. Amidst the push for scale, some developers are advocating for the \"small web,\" arguing that decentralized, independent spaces remain a vital, often overlooked, component of the internet.\n\n### Quick Hits\n*   **Regulatory & Legal:** The SEC is reportedly considering a shift toward twice-yearly earnings reports. Simultaneously, the long-running Live Nation/Ticketmaster antitrust trial has resumed.\n*   **Software & Hardware:** Picsart has launched an agent marketplace for creators, while Aqara’s latest Matter-compatible camera signals further integration in the smart home space.\n*   **Industry Sentiment:** New research suggests that every additional layer of corporate review increases project latency by a factor of 10x, serving as a cautionary tale for organizational efficiency. \n*   **Lifestyle & Deals:** Consumers can currently find notable discounts across several sectors, including up to 50% off select Ecovacs robot vacuums and significant promotional incentives for Sam’s Club, Expedia, and KitchenAid products.','[{\"title\": \"Leanstral: Open-source agent for trustworthy coding and formal proof engineering\", \"url\": \"https://mistral.ai/news/leanstral\"}, {\"title\": \"The unlikely story of Teardown Multiplayer\", \"url\": \"https://blog.voxagon.se/2026/03/13/teardown-multiplayer.html\"}, {\"title\": \"Meta\\u2019s renewed commitment to jemalloc\", \"url\": \"https://engineering.fb.com/2026/03/02/data-infrastructure/investing-in-infrastructure-metas-renewed-commitment-to-jemalloc/\"}, {\"title\": \"The \\u201csmall web\\u201d is bigger than you might think\", \"url\": \"https://kevinboone.me/small_web_is_big.html\"}, {\"title\": \"Every layer of review makes you 10x slower\", \"url\": \"https://apenwarr.ca/log/20260316\"}, {\"title\": \"Picsart now allows creators to \\u2018hire\\u2019 AI assistants through agent marketplace\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/16/picsart-now-allows-creators-to-hire-ai-assistants-through-agent-marketplace/\"}, {\"title\": \"SEC eyes shift to twice-yearly earnings reports\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/16/sec-eyes-shift-to-twice-yearly-earnings-reports/\"}, {\"title\": \"Nvidia\\u2019s version of OpenClaw could solve its biggest problem: security\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/16/nvidias-version-of-openclaw-could-solve-its-biggest-problem-security/\"}, {\"title\": \"Jensen Huang just put Nvidia\\u2019s Blackwell and Vera Rubin sales projections into the $1 trillion stratosphere\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/16/jensen-just-put-nvidias-blackwell-and-vera-rubin-sales-projections-into-the-1-trillion-stratosphere/\"}, {\"title\": \"Warren presses Pentagon over decision to grant xAI access to classified networks\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/16/warren-presses-pentagon-over-decision-to-grant-xai-access-to-classified-networks/\"}, {\"title\": \"Hands on with Aqara\\u2019s new Matter-compatible camera\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/895326/aqara-g350-matter-camera-samsung-smartthings-hands-on-revie