action to its own strategic advantage, pointedly ignoring requests regarding the Hormuz Strait.\n\nDomestically, the political environment is equally fraught. A brewing administrative crisis regarding a potential DHS shutdown has airline CEOs sounding the alarm on the brink of domestic travel collapse. In the political arena, Governor J.B. Pritzker is aggressively targeting the Trump campaign, aiming to tip the scales in the upcoming Senate race.\n\n### Tech & Innovation: The Enterprise Shift\n\nThe enterprise artificial intelligence landscape is undergoing a structural pivot. Mistral AI has launched \"Forge,\" signaling a strategic commitment to \"build-your-own AI\" solutions, positioning the company to compete directly with giants like OpenAI and Anthropic for the enterprise market. This move comes as the U.S. Justice Department has expressed significant reservations regarding the integration of Anthropic’s systems into sensitive warfighting infrastructure.\n\nBeyond the enterprise, the tech community continues to grapple with the ethics and utility of AI integration. Garry Tan’s implementation of \"Claude Code\" has sparked a fierce debate over the boundaries of automated coding, while Apple has initiated a critical background security update to mitigate a persistent Safari vulnerability. On the consumer front, Kagi is making a notable bid to preserve the \"small web\" by bringing its human-centric search experience to mobile platforms.\n\n### Quick Hits: Notable Mentions\n\n*   **Engineering & Theory:** For those interested in the fundamentals, new literature has emerged on the intricacies of JPEG compression and a detailed retrospective on a homebrew CPU build, alongside a tribute to the foundational computer science legacy of Tony Hoare.\n*   **Corporate & Legal:** Kalshi is facing severe legal headwinds as Arizona files the first criminal charges against the platform, alleging it operates an \"illegal gambling business.\"\n*   **Consumer Tech & Entertainment:** Remedy’s *Firebreak* is approaching its final major update, while Spotify is introducing an \"Exclusive Mode\" for Windows users to satisfy audiophile demands. Conversely, Ikea’s foray into the smart home space remains a work in progress, highlighting the friction between vision and execution.\n*   **Economic Opportunities:** For the savvy consumer, March brings a flurry of promotional activity, including significant discounts on Beats Studio Pro headphones and various retail and service incentives across platforms like Chewy, DoorDash, NordVPN, and AT&T.','[{\"title\": \"JPEG Compression\", \"url\": \"https://www.sophielwang.com/blog/jpeg\"}, {\"title\": \"Write up of my homebrew CPU build\", \"url\": \"https://willwarren.com/2026/03/12/building-my-own-cpu-part-3-from-simulation-to-hardware/\"}, {\"title\": \"Mistral AI Releases Forge\", \"url\": \"https://mistral.ai/news/forge\"}, {\"title\": \"A Decade of Slug\", \"url\": \"https://terathon.com/blog/decade-slug.html\"}, {\"title\": \"Celebrating Tony Hoare\'s mark on computer science\", \"url\": \"https://bertrandmeyer.com/2026/03/16/celebrating-tony-hoares-mark-on-computer-science/\"}, {\"title\": \"Kalshi\\u2019s legal troubles pile up, as Arizona files first ever criminal charges over \\u2018illegal gambling business\\u2019\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/17/kalshis-legal-troubles-pile-up-as-arizona-files-first-ever-criminal-charges-over-illegal-gambling-business/\"}, {\"title\": \"Mistral bets on \\u2018build-your-own AI\\u2019 as it takes on OpenAI, Anthropic in the enterprise\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/17/mistral-forge-nvidia-gtc-build-your-own-ai-enterprise/\"}, {\"title\": \"Why Garry Tan\\u2019s Claude Code setup has gotten so much love, and hate\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/17/why-garry-tans-claude-code-setup-has-gotten-so-much-love-and-hate/\"}, {\"title\": \"Apple rolls out first \\u2018background security\\u2019 update for iPhones, iPads, and Macs to