o/quotable/2026/3/18/us-distraction-in-the-middle-east-is-in-chinas?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Middle East crisis live: Iran vows revenge for killing of security chief; Israel strikes central Beirut - The Guardian\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"King of Illinois: Pritzker swings Senate race as he targets Trump - Politico\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMimAFBVV95cUxQQ2dPRHJkSFRLMHVZNTdWT3VsRDh1YkNjZ2dyUTBGUWxhcm1nQ05tRDUySVJCZmVoZjItS21lX01jNVdUZmpLMzRrZ1FfM0I3Um1fV2ZDblc2TlAyY2ZxdzVWclNsLTkxWVA4LWJTZmhYeE9wWldIRVltTTV4aV9UX2FMRVhxMl9FYXpzTTRRZW0tck51dERHcg?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"In His Resignation Letter, Joe Kent Spoke About the Death of His Wife - The New York Times\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMijAFBVV95cUxPdjZ4Z0FIVW9seHByOVRLYkFyZVBsZUVqUkpVN3haUWFZTnpWTkZfOUo3WHRHMHRVVkhRUU9OcWl6YWpPSUh4TXkzRnhUemw5cmRPd3lvaV9kc0RlR09uMWZTSjMyQ3Y3ZzJLbWtiMTVzekJQM2RSei1xdDNZd2owdnZqeUZ5bTZyNUIxSA?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"China ignores Trump\\u2019s Hormuz request as the Iran war deepens and his Beijing trip slips - AP News\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMijwFBVV95cUxOald4V19aSzJyQXlVZG1ZVnF4WHViSE16ZU8wVC1FU2pyekxWZkpjbm1oUV85MmRfajZ6NkNxY1MwYWxMYVRYamROOXJTUndxWlE1LXEzaTBrQk8tcW15NjBZRHpNQk1oLTRTZXlvQ3V4SnpiUExiMVJ1ZnNFbjkxUVJzZ21QbC0zTzNTZVJOUQ?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Airline CEOs Demand \\u201cImmediate\\u201d Action as Democrats\\u2019 DHS Shutdown Pushes Air Travel to the Brink - The White House (.gov)\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.?oc=5\"}]','2026-03-18 09:00:12'),(14,'Daily Planet - March 19, 2026','### The Global Outlook: Escalating Conflict in the Middle East\n\nThe geopolitical landscape remains dominated by the intensifying conflict involving Iran, Israel, and the Gulf states. Following an attack on an Israeli gas field, the war has entered a volatile new phase, prompting a retaliatory response from the Gulf and heightening regional instability. Oil prices have surged past $110 per barrel, fueling concerns of a sustained energy crisis across Europe. \n\nWhile US intelligence leadership asserts that the Iranian regime, though \"degraded,\" remains tactically intact, the US is reportedly weighing the deployment of thousands of additional troops to the region. Amidst this, President Trump has suspended the Jones Act for 60 days to stabilize supply chains and has issued sharp warnings, threatening to \"massively blow up\" Iranian gas infrastructure should Iran target Qatar.\n\n---\n\n### Tech & Innovation: The Agents of Change\n\nThe technology sector is pivoting rapidly toward agentic AI and infrastructure optimization. \n\n*   **The End of the App?** Nothing CEO Carl Pei has signaled a paradigm shift, predicting that standalone smartphone apps will eventually be superseded by autonomous AI agents capable of handling complex user tasks.\n*   **Infrastructure & Security:** Meta is currently grappling with the challenges of maintaining control over \"rogue\" AI agents. Meanwhile, efficiency remains a priority: Nvidia’s *Greenboost* is emerging as a solution to extend GPU VRAM using system resources, and Multiverse Computing is bringing compressed, high-efficiency AI models into the mainstream.\n*   **Defense & Industry:** The sector continues to see significant capital inflows for high-stakes intelligence; two Palantir veterans have emerged from stealth mode with $30 million in backing from Sequoia.\n\n---\n\n### Quick Hits: Notable Mentions\n\n*   **Policy & Governance:** The FBI is under scrutiny for the warrantless purchase of American location data, while Congress has opened a contentious hearing regarding the potential overhaul of Section 230 internet laws.\n*   **Urban Development:** In a rare piece of positive domestic data, Austin, Texas, has demonstrated that aggressive housing construction is a direct and effective lever for cooling rental markets.\n*   **International Affairs:** The US is navigating a legislative battle over the status of international students, with new bills aiming to protect their visas against potential administrative threats. Meanwhile, in France, concerns are mounting over the potential for far-right gains in key mayoral elections.\n*   **Cultural & Miscellaneous:** \n    *   **Tech Humor:** Sam Altman’s public acknowledgment of software engineers has triggered a wave of viral memes across the developer community.\n    *   **Retail:** A variety of significant discounts are currently available, including deals on hardware from Hoto and major promotions across retailers like Best Buy, Nike, and Home Depot.\n    *   **Accountability:** Oregon institutions are currently reconciling with the removal of Cesar Chavez’s name from public facilities following a report alleging sexual abuse.','[{\"title\": \"Conway\'s Game of Life, in real life\", \"url\": \"https://lcamtuf.substack.com/p/conways-game-of-life-in-real-life\"}, {\"title\": \"Nvidia greenboost: transparently extend GPU VRAM using system RAM/NVMe\", \"url\": \"https://gitlab.com/IsolatedOctopi/nvidia_greenboost\"}, {\"title\": \"Warranty Void If Regenerated\", \"url\": \"https://nearzero.software/p/warranty-void-if-regenerated\"}, {\"title\": \"Translate Garry Tan\'s LinkedIn-speak to plain English\", \"url\": \"https://github.com/garrytan/gstack/pull/213\"}, {\"title\": \"Austin\\u2019s surge of new housing construction drove down rents\", \"url\": \"https://www.pew.org/en/research-and-analysis/articles/2026/03/18/austins-surge-of-new-housing-construction-drove-down-rents\"}, {\"title\": \"Multiverse Computing pushes its compressed AI models into the mainstream\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/19/multiverse-computing-pushes-its-compressed-ai-models-into-the-mainstream/\"}, {\"title\": \"Two Palantir veterans just came out of stealth with $30 million and a Sequoia stamp of approval\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/18/two-palantir-veterans-just-came-out-of-stealth-with-30-million-a