"Cesar Chavez abuse allegations: Dolores Huerta speaks with ABC News on camera for first time after sharing - ABC7 Los Angeles\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Teenager among first to be executed over Iran\'s anti-government protests - BBC\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMiWkFVX3lxTE1QNy1rRzhSaFAtUGd1LU5GeU0wbFhpQkNYZ1BWNWdJbDBzTlZqZHF5SFluY3Awb09KS19peEJFay1OOG1LMmN2c1NvUm9aRHhkdk1jWDhXTGpuZw?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Trump Says He Won\\u2019t Send Troops to Iran but Leaves Wiggle Room - The New York Times\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMigwFBVV95cUxNaG9STnkwdWFNYTlhZkZlNjlDVUFqU1VxX0t6ZVlxVlY0NFVHb2lrY3VUeVNYRHE5a1FNRjVtZjJRNGgxeGxQbGRVLU5SYkIzREMxeFV2SkxKVk5PVk1abUJoZFY3a2Nicnd1SnBQWl9xbkhBM3FnbWRzUzJpSldSZGpWMA?oc=5\"}]','2026-03-20 09:00:58'),(16,'Daily Planet - March 21, 2026','### Global Affairs: Conflict, Diplomacy, and Climate Extremes\n\nThe shadow of the ongoing Iran-U.S. conflict continues to dominate the global discourse, even as signs of a potential thaw emerge. While the administration hints at \"winding down\" the war, the region remains a pressure cooker; recent analyses indicate that Iranian strikes on U.S.-utilized bases have resulted in $800 million in damages. In a pragmatic, if controversial, move to combat soaring domestic fuel prices, the U.S. has begun lifting sanctions on millions of barrels of Iranian oil. Concurrently, Iran has signaled a willingness to allow Japanese vessels passage through the Strait of Hormuz. Despite these diplomatic overtures, the geopolitical atmosphere remains fraught as millions mark the Nowruz holiday under the persistent cloud of war.\n\nIn other international developments, an oil pipeline dispute between Ukraine and Hungary is threatening the stability of critical EU loans. Across the Atlantic, an aid flotilla from Mexico is currently en route to Cuba. Meanwhile, France is bracing for high-stakes mayoral elections, with Socialist parties working to maintain their strongholds in Paris.\n\nDomestically, the environment and infrastructure are showing signs of strain. Arizona has shattered records for the hottest March temperature in U.S. history, while a dam on Oahu, Hawaii, faces \"imminent failure\" following severe conditions that have already swept people into the water.\n\n### Tech & Innovation: The AI Arms Race and Corporate Reckoning\n\nThe intersection of artificial intelligence and national security remains a flashpoint. A new court filing has exposed a jarring discrepancy between the Pentagon and Anthropic, revealing that officials confirmed their relationship was \"nearly aligned\" just one week after the Trump administration declared the partnership defunct. Anthropic has since moved to preemptively deny allegations that it could sabotage its own tools during wartime.\n\nThe corporate landscape remains equally turbulent. A jury has delivered a verdict against Elon Musk, finding that he intentionally misled Twitter investors during his attempts to abandon the acquisition, citing his \"stupid tweets\" as a primary driver of shareholder losses. \n\nIn the hardware and software sectors, the \"bloat\" era of AI is facing a slight correction as Microsoft rolls back several Copilot features within Windows. Nvidia continues its aggressive $1 trillion bet on the future of computing—showcasing innovations like *NemoClaw* and *Robot Olaf* at GTC—though its latest DLSS 5 technology is meeting resistance from developers and gamers alike. Meanwhile, the gaming industry is looking toward a sustainable future, with the upcoming Nintendo Switch 2 potentially serving as a benchmark for user-replaceable batteries, while Sony pivots toward AI-generated frame interpolation for its future PlayStation catalog.\n\n### Quick Hits\n\n*   **Connectivity:** The Starlink Mini has received a meaningful hardware update, improving its battery-powered performance for remote use.\n*   **Media & Moderation:** A significant automated moderation error at Tumblr resulted in a wave of panicked, accidental account bans. Elsewhere, a federal judge has ruled in favor of independent journalism, striking down press restrictions previously imposed by the Pentagon.\n*   **Prediction Markets:** The legal and ethical integrity of prediction markets is being questioned, with Kalshi facing a temporary ban in Nevada amidst broader scrutiny of the industry.\n*   **Cultural Notes:** As interest in legacy memes remains high, a study suggests that the cultural ubiquity of Chuck Norris memes has far outpaced actual viewership of his filmography. For those seeking travel etiquette, a new glossary detailing the specific *faux pas* associated with chopsticks in Japan serves as a vital guide for the culturally curious.\n*   **Amazon Rumors:** Industry chatter regarding a new Amazon smartphone persists, though market analysts remain skeptical of its necessity in an already saturated hardware ecosystem.','[{\"title\": \"OpenCode \\u2013 Open source AI coding agent\", \"url\": \"https://opencode.ai/\"}, {\"title\": \"Mamba-3\", \"url\": \"https://www.together.ai/blog/mamba-3\"}, {\"title\": \"FFmpeg 101 (2024)\", \"url\": \"https://blogs.igalia.com/llepage/ffmpeg-101/\"}, {\"title\": \"Molly Guard\", \"url\": \"https://bookofjoe2.blogspot.com/2026/02/molly-guard.html\"}, {\"title\": \"A Japanese glossary of chopsticks faux pas\", \"url\": \"https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-data/h01362/\"}, {\"title\": \"New court filing reveals Pentagon told Anthropic the two sides were nearly aligned \\u2014 a week after Trump declared the relationship kaput\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/20/new-court-filing-reveals-pentagon-told-anthropic-the-two-sides-were-nearly-aligned-a-week-after-trump-declared-the-relationship-kaput/\"}, {\"title\": \"Elon Musk misled Twitter investors while trying to get out of acquisition, jury says\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/20/elon-musk-misled-twitter-investors-while-trying-to-ge