rt Mueller, who probed Trump as special counsel, dies at 81 - Axios\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMiYkFVX3lxTFBWLUdDM0pfcEpfdk9tTU04YzBNVDM5aG1Qa205Q0RwQllpLUtjcGdlQnlaNEdySUFuTUItSmt1Mnc0MVVSRExveEI0dm0tVFlwUF9ibUR3eWJZWDJpRjNpdXBR?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Trump says he will order federal immigration officers to help with airport security unless Democrats end shutdown - PBS\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Cuba\\u2019s power grid collapses leaving it without electricity for the 3rd time this month - AP News\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMihwFBVV95cUxPdWtXZHY0REo3Y2hsLXpvbWNEVkRiRkdjN0VaU3RYenFPdF9oTmV0MXk2NUloYUgyampoSFhuUlRiMG9PZWgyLWoxVWV6OWFjckJ0ZlJGQ0lFczlrSkxETnR3YVlXZzJVaHdfTTV5X2QydlVZUVVUb2U5dzNFUWVGSmY4VEc0VmM?oc=5\"}]','2026-03-22 09:00:53'),(18,'Daily Planet - March 23, 2026','### Global Current Events: Heightened Geopolitical Instability\n\nThe international landscape faces a precarious weekend as market sentiment and security concerns converge. Financial markets are exhibiting volatility as the conflict between the United States and Iran shows signs of dangerous escalation, with the IEA warning that a severe global energy crisis may be imminent. This geopolitical strain is echoed by Israel’s expansion of military operations against Hezbollah in Lebanon and reports of ongoing violence in the West Bank.\n\nDomestically, the administration is set to shift security priorities, with reports indicating that ICE agents will be deployed to airports starting Monday—a move likely to further complicate the travel environment, which is already experiencing significant friction following a ground collision at LaGuardia Airport. Meanwhile, in Europe, French politics remain in flux; while the Socialists have secured key cities, the far-right is aggressively claiming momentum, signaling a turbulent lead-up to future presidential cycles. In the Pacific, the National Guard remains active in Hawaii to assist with recovery efforts following severe flooding in Oahu.\n\n### Tech and Innovation: Infrastructure and Industry Shifts\n\nThe intersection of industrial policy and artificial intelligence is reshaping the tech landscape. Elon Musk has announced the development of the \"Terafab\" chip plant in Austin, Texas, a strategic move aimed at vertical integration for SpaceX and Tesla. This comes alongside significant movement in the AI sector, as Cursor has acknowledged that its latest coding model utilizes Moonshot AI’s Kimi, underscoring the growing reliance on cross-pollination within the large language model ecosystem.\n\nRegulatory pressure continues to evolve: the SEC has officially shuttered its four-year investigation into the electric vehicle startup Faraday Future, a notable reprieve for the company. Meanwhile, concerns regarding the integrity of digital and creative outputs remain high; developers of *Crimson Desert* were forced to issue an apology following public backlash over the use of AI-generated art, illustrating the ongoing cultural tension between efficiency-driven automation and traditional craftsmanship.\n\n### Quick Hits\n\n*   **Cybersecurity & Retro-Tech:** A fascinating look at hardware security surfaces with research on the possibility of gaining root access via a cigarette lighter (DRAM EMFI), while retro-gaming enthusiasts are revisiting the exceptional optimization standards of *RollerCoaster Tycoon*.\n*   **Media & Digital Living:** The debate over digital autonomy continues with a focus on the \"POSSE\" (Publish on your Own Site, Syndicate Elsewhere) philosophy. Conversely, parenting tech is experimenting with analog-inspired solutions, such as the \"Tin Can\" landline for children.\n*   **Culture & Consumerism:** *Topical Dancer* is garnering critical acclaim for its blend of politics and rhythm. For those managing the home front, Amazon’s Big Spring Sale is live, though tech-savvy readers might be more interested in the latest guides o