urbulence. Markwayne Mullin has been confirmed to lead the Department of Homeland Security, yet the agency’s funding remains in limbo as the administration pushes to link budgetary measures to the SAVE America Act. In other critical news, investigations are underway following a fatal plane crash at LaGuardia, and the state of Hawaii is beginning to assess the extensive damage wrought by recent catastrophic flooding.\n\n### Tech & Innovation: The AGI Threshold and Industry Shifts\n\nThe conversation in Silicon Valley has reached a new plateau of intensity, with Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang declaring that the industry has effectively achieved Artificial General Intelligence (AGI). This bold claim arrives alongside a wave of tactical shifts in the tech sector:\n\n*   **Investment & Scrutiny:** The venture capital ecosystem is seeing significant movement, with the CEO of Air Street Capital launching a substantial $232M fund, and leaders from rival prediction markets Kalshi and Polymarket unexpectedly joining forces to back a $35M VC fund. Conversely, the industry is grappling with reputational risks, as Delve halts demonstrations following allegations of \"fake compliance,\" leading to a quiet scrubbing of investment documentation by its backers.\n*   **Regulatory & Corporate Maneuvers:** The U.S. government has enacted a ban on non-U.S. manufactured consumer routers, signaling a tightened stance on hardware infrastructure security. Meanwhile, cultural tensions from the previous decade persist; Emil Michael, now a senior Pentagon official, has signaled a lasting personal rift with the investors who facilitated his and Travis Kalanick’s departure from Uber.\n*   **The AI Frontier:** Practical applications for AI continue to emerge, notably *ProofShot*, which provides coding agents with visual confirmation of the interfaces they build, and *MagicAudio*, a new tool for sophisticated noise and background removal.\n\n### Quick Hits\n\n*   **Infrastructure & Nostalgia:** For the home-tinkerer, there is a fascinating guide on discreetly integrating legacy apartment intercoms with Apple Home. For the web historian, Opera is celebrating its 30th anniversary with a project allowing users to \"rewind\" the web to the aesthetics and limitations of 1996.\n*   **Global Sports:** Eritrea is breaking an 18-year hiatus from the Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) qualifiers, with a match against Eswatini marking a significant return to the international stage.\n*   **Economic Adjustments:** China has moved to mitigate the economic impact on its citizenry by cooling fuel price hikes, a strategic effort to reduce the burden on drivers amidst global volatility.\n*   **Consumer Pulse:** As the spring retail cycle begins, various deep discounts are currently circulating for products ranging from Sony hardware and Brooks footwear to wellness products from Ulta and home furnishings at Design Within Reach. Additionally, a billionaire-backed startup is making waves in the bio-tech space with efforts to develop synthetic \"organ sacks\" as a potential humane alternative to traditional animal testing.','[{\"title\": \"Box of Secrets: Discreetly modding an apartment intercom to work with Apple Home\", \"url\": \"https://www.jackhogan.me/blog/box-of-secrets/\"}, {\"title\": \"Log File Viewer for the Terminal\", \"url\": \"https://lnav.org/\"}, {\"title\": \"Show HN: ProofShot \\u2013 Give AI coding agents eyes to verify the UI they build\", \"url\": \"https://proofshot.argil.io/\"}, {\"title\": \"Opera: Rewind The Web to 1996 (Opera at 30)\", \"url\": \"https://www.web-rewind.com\"}, {\"title\": \"MagicAudio \\u2013 Free Noise, Echo and Background Music Remover\", \"url\": \"https://magicaudio.pro/\"}, {\"title\": \"Delve halts demos, Insight Partners scrubs investment post amid \\u2018fake compliance\\u2019 allegations\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/23/delve-halts-demos-insight-partners-scrubs-investment-post-amid-fake-compliance-allegations/\"}, {\"title\