pe of damage from Hawaii\\u2019s floods becomes clearer - AP News\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMigwFBVV95cUxObUEzLTk5ZGdYVXo0bWdSOTR6U3JicklnM3ZqdTVUcEJPWVFjb2xrOUJKUkt4Q2Y5X05HX2ppQXVudEFEQzJlRWFPaEJEZ2NXQkplSk5aQWU1cE4zWTZJWDFBaFVYZGJ2Q3FGTW4wSlBQSDc0V29TTXk5d21pV0JpdzhmMA?oc=5\"}]','2026-03-24 09:00:50'),(20,'Daily Planet - March 25, 2026','### The Daily Planet\n\n#### **Global Conflict & Geopolitical Instability**\nThe precarious standoff in the Middle East has intensified, as the United States military deploys paratroopers to the region amidst escalating tensions with Iran. Diplomatic channels appear strained; while the U.S. has proposed ceasefire terms, Iran’s Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps (IRGC) has aggressively dismissed the offer, warning Washington and Israel against mislabeling their military position as a negotiated agreement. Domestically, the political fallout is manifesting in public sentiment: a new Reuters/Ipsos poll indicates that President Trump’s approval rating has plummeted to a record low of 36%, fueled by surging energy costs tied to the unfolding conflict. Meanwhile, in Eastern Europe, a cycle of retaliatory strikes between Russia and Ukraine has successfully crippled power grids, leaving over half a million civilians in the dark.\n\n#### **Tech, Policy, and the Corporate Frontier**\nThe tech industry faces a reckoning with both regulation and aggressive capital deployment. In a landmark courtroom defeat, Meta has been ordered to pay $375 million following a jury verdict that found the company misled users regarding the safety of its products—a ruling in New Mexico that is being closely monitored by jurisdictions nationwide. Amidst this regulatory pressure, Kleiner Perkins is signaling a heavy double-down on the AI sector with a fresh $3.5 billion capital infusion. Elsewhere, Amazon continues its push into robotics with the acquisition of a startup specializing in kid-sized humanoid units, while the U.S. government moves to restrict foreign-made routers, citing national security concerns.\n\n#### **Quick Hits**\n*   **Humanitarian Concerns:** A gruesome discovery in Kenya—dozens of bodies, primarily infants—has prompted international shock and a search for answers.\n*   **Corporate Moves:** BlackRock CEO Larry Fink has issued a stark warning that oil prices hitting $150 could trigger a global recession. \n*   **Political Shifts:** A significant upset occurred in Florida, where a Democrat secured a House seat in a district containing Mar-a-Lago, while in Denmark, the Prime Minister faces a historic parliamentary hurdle following the party\'s weakest election showing since 1903.\n*   **Innovation & Culture:** NASA is eyeing a $20 billion lunar base fueled by nuclear power; meanwhile, the tech nostalgia market thrives with the release of the BB-777 boombox.\n*   **The Archives:** Survivors of Jeffrey Epstein have provided harrowing testimony to the BBC, detailing the psychological terror inflicted upon them.\n*   **Tech Tidbits:** Users of Instagram and Facebook should expect a surge in affiliate shopping content as Meta pivots its monetization strategy for Reels.','[{\"title\": \"I Forked Httpx\", \"url\": \"https://tildeweb.nl/~michiel/httpxyz.html\"}, {\"title\": \"TurboQuant: Redefining AI efficiency with extreme compression\", \"url\": \"https://research.google/blog/turboquant-redefining-ai-efficiency-with-extreme-compression/\"}, {\"title\": \"VitruvianOS \\u2013 Desktop Linux Inspired by the BeOS\", \"url\": \"https://v-os.dev\"}, {\"title\": \"Goodbye to Sora\", \"url\": \"https://twitter.com/soraofficialapp/status/2036532795984715896\"}, {\"title\": \"Flighty Airports\", \"url\": \"https://flighty.com/airports\"}, {\"title\": \"A former Thiel fellow\\u2019s startup just launched a drone it says can replace police helicopters\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/24/a-former-thiel-fellows-startup-just-launched-a-drone-it-says-can-replace-police-helicopters/\"}, {