social media addiction, and the United Nations has formally recognized the enslavement of Africans as the \"gravest crime against humanity.\"\n\n### Tech & Innovation: Autonomy, Security, and Hardware\n\nThe autonomous transportation sector is seeing significant expansion. In a move to accelerate European adoption, Uber is partnering with Pony AI and Verne to launch the continent\'s first robotaxi service. Meanwhile, a lesser-known Croatian startup is also entering the competitive robotaxi market, leveraging a strategic collaboration with Uber.\n\nIn the realm of AI and cybersecurity, the industry continues to grapple with governance and safety. Project LiteLLM, a prominent AI project, has been compromised by malware, raising questions about the security compliance protocols of third-party firms like Delve. Concurrently, the debate surrounding the \"AI skills gap\" suggests that power users are increasingly distancing themselves from the general workforce, a trend reflected by the $25M funding of Deccan AI, which is scaling its operations by sourcing expertise from India. Looking toward long-term research, the ARC-AGI-3 prize marks the next frontier in measuring true machine intelligence.\n\nOn the consumer hardware front, innovation in efficiency is yielding results. Intel and LG Display have potentially set a new benchmark for laptop battery life with their latest integration, promising a significant shift in mobile computing endurance.\n\n### Quick Hits\n\n*   **Science & Environment:** Earthquake researchers have identified that overplowing at experimental farms is critically weakening soil stability, highlighting the often-overlooked environmental consequences of intensive agriculture.\n*   **Culture:** A retrospective look at The Ramones offers a sobering economic reality: the band’s commercial legacy was defined far more by merchandise—specifically T-shirts—than by their recorded music catalog.\n*   **Amazon Big Spring Sale:** For those seeking retail value, notable discounts are currently active on Sonos Ace headphones and the Fanttik X9 Pro tire inflator.\n*   **Digital Tools & Subscriptions:** A variety of promotional incentives are currently available for professional services, including 20% off Squarespace annual plans, 10% off LLC formations via LegalZoom, and significant equipment deals through Therabody and Lenovo.','[{\"title\": \"Personal Encyclopedias\", \"url\": \"https://whoami.wiki/blog/personal-encyclopedias\"}, {\"title\": \"Running Tesla Model 3\'s computer on my desk using parts from crashed cars\", \"url\": \"https://bugs.xdavidhu.me/tesla/2026/03/23/running-tesla-model-3s-computer-on-my-desk-using-parts-from-crashed-cars/\"}, {\"title\": \"ARC-AGI-3\", \"url\": \"https://arcprize.org/arc-agi/3\"}, {\"title\": \"Earthquake scientists reveal how overplowing weakens soil at experimental farm\", \"url\": \"https://www.washington.edu/news/2026/03/19/earthquake-scientists-reveal-how-overplowing-weakens-soil-at-experimental-farm/\"}, {\"title\": \"The truth that haunts the Ramones: \'They sold more T-shirts than records\'\", \"url\": \"https://english.elpais.com/culture/2026-03-17/the-uncomfortable-truth-that-will-always-haunt-the-ramones-they-sold-more-t-shirts-than-records.html\"}, {\"title\": \"A little-known Croatian startup is coming for the robotaxi market with help from Uber\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/26/a-little-known-croatian-startup-is-coming-for-the-robotaxi-market-with-help-from-uber/\"}, {\"title\": \"The least surprising chapter of the Manus story is what\\u2019s happening right now\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/25/the-least-surprising-chapter-of-the-manus-story-is-whats-happening-right-now/\"}, {\"title\": \"Mercor competitor Deccan AI raises $25M, sources experts from India\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/25/deccan-ai-raises-25m-as-ai-training-push-relies-on-india-based-workforce/\"}, {\"title\": \"Delve did the security compliance on LiteLLM, an