harden, with former President Trump issuing direct threats against Iran’s energy infrastructure, including desalination plants—a strategy that experts warn could have catastrophic humanitarian implications for the broader Middle East. Concurrently, reports indicate an attack on a Kuwaiti-flagged oil tanker, underscoring the peril to global energy transit corridors. \n\nIn related regional developments, the humanitarian crisis in Sudan continues to draw international concern, with reports of systemic sexual violence, while in the Israel-Palestine theater, violence persists and holy sites remain shuttered, complicating any path toward stability. Domestically, the U.S. political temperature is rising, with the Supreme Court set to deliberate on birthright citizenship this week, and a notable escalation in Silicon Valley’s congressional race.\n\n***\n\n### **Tech & Innovation: Security, Silicon, and Shifts**\n\n*   **Cybersecurity Breach:** Axios has confirmed a compromise of their NPM packages, where malicious versions were injected to drop a remote access trojan. Developers are urged to audit their dependencies immediately.\n*   **Edge AI Acceleration:** Ollama has integrated MLX support on Apple Silicon in preview, marking a meaningful optimization for local large language model inference on Mac hardware. \n*   **AI Efficiency:** New initiatives, such as the *Universal Claude.md* repository, are surfacing as developers aggressively seek to optimize token output costs in an increasingly expensive AI operational environment.\n*   **Data Models:** Google Research has debuted *TimesFM*, a 200M-parameter foundation model specifically engineered for time-series forecasting with an expansive 16k context window, signaling a robust move into specialized industrial AI.\n\n***\n\n### **Quick Hits: Market Movements & Trends**\n\n*   **Corporate Realignment:** In a stark display of the cooling startup market, Allbirds is finalizing a sale for $39 million—a fraction of the capital raised during its IPO. Meanwhile, the Roblox competitor *Rec Room* is shutting down after a decade of operation and 150 million users.\n*   **The Future of Service:** Airbnb is diversifying its hospitality footprint by introducing a private car pick-up service, signaling an effort to capture more of the travel value chain.\n*   **Workforce Sentiment:** A recent Quinnipiac poll suggests that roughly 15% of the American workforce would be open to the prospect of an AI manager, highlighting a slow but measurable shift in professional perception toward automation.\n*   **Aerospace Uncertainty:** The discourse surrounding the safety of the Artemis II mission has intensified, while private space ventures face continued reliability challenges, evidenced by the inexplicable explosion of another Starlink satellite.\n*   **Consumer Picks:** Amazon’s \"Big Spring Sale\" remains in focus, with notable discounts on UWB-enabled smart locks from Aqara and gym-ready audio gear from Beats, while WIRED continues to highlight essential categories ranging from air purifiers to hearing protection.','[{\"title\": \"Axios compromised on NPM \\u2013 Malicious versions drop remote access trojan\", \"url\": \"https://www.stepsecurity.io/blog/axios-compromised-on-npm-malicious-versions-drop-remote-access-trojan\"}, {\"title\": \"Ollama is now powered by MLX on Apple Silicon in preview\", \"url\": \"https://ollama.com/blog/mlx\"}, {\"title\": \"Artemis II is not safe to fly\", \"url\": \"https://idlewords.com/2026/03/artemis_ii_is_not_safe_to_fly.htm\"}, {\"title\": \"Universal Claude.md \\u2013 cut Claude output tokens\", \"url\": \"https://github.com/drona23/claude-token-efficient\"}, {\"title\": \"Google\'s 200M-parameter time-series foundation model with 16k context\", \"url\": \"https://github.com/google-research/timesfm\"}, {\"title\": \"Airbnb is introducing a private car pick-up service\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/31/airbnb-private-car-pick-up-service-welcome-pickups/