"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMijwFBVV95cUxQcEpCUHRHMDU3bklKS253eDdHWnplV2VsaG9fOG1NSGpZb1ljdFRETFpXTmo5S3YzVzVmV3ZXemREUkVmakZpeEhobGU2WW1rOUd2aGFuQmF3cEZjSDB0cjM5clYwdFZfMnJ0aUliN0YxdmdsMlZPeEF0T1pVbUtCQ19NbDJpTXc4cDB5LTdwcw?oc=5\"}]','2026-03-31 09:00:59'),(27,'Daily Planet - April 01, 2026','### The Daily Planet | April 1, 2026\n\n#### Global Crisis: The Escalation of the Iran Conflict\nThe geopolitical landscape is rapidly deteriorating as the conflict involving Iran widens. Reports indicate that Iranian-linked strikes have caused fires in Kuwait and Bahrain, resulting in fatalities in the UAE. Amidst this, the security situation remains volatile; a U.S. journalist, Shelly Kittleson, has been kidnapped in Baghdad—an act linked to Iranian militants—and there are disturbing reports of children being utilized in security roles within the conflict zones.\n\nWhile China attempts to position itself as a diplomatic intermediary, the efficacy of these efforts remains in doubt. In Washington, the administration’s strategy is in flux; President Trump has suggested a U.S. withdrawal from the region within weeks, even as he faces domestic legal battles, including a judge’s stay on his White House ballroom project and an upcoming Supreme Court hearing regarding birthright citizenship. Meanwhile, in the Levant, Israel has signaled its intent to maintain control over portions of southern Lebanon post-Hezbollah, further complicating the prospects for de-escalation.\n\n#### Tech & Innovation: AI Governance and Corporate Shifts\nThe tech sector is grappling with significant security and structural challenges. Anthropic has found itself in the spotlight—and at a precarious crossroad—following a source code leak that unveiled an always-on AI agent and \"pet\"-like features, even as the company experiences a period of intense industry scrutiny. Security remains the paramount concern: an open-source project, LiteLLM, was compromised, leading to a direct cyberattack on the firm Mercor. Furthermore, Apple is preemptively responding to the \"DarkSword\" hacking tool by issuing rare backported security patches for iOS 18.\n\nIn the enterprise space, Salesforce is implementing a massive, AI-centric overhaul of Slack, rolling out 30 new features aimed at productivity. Conversely, the \"future of mobility\" faces a transparency crisis; major robotaxi operators are refusing to disclose the frequency of remote intervention required for their autonomous vehicles, an issue underscored by a recent outage in China that left passengers stranded on active highways. \n\n#### Quick Hits: Notable Mentions\n*   **Demographics & Democracy:** India has officially commenced the world’s largest population census, though the process is mired in controversy as allegations of gerrymandering in Assam threaten to dilute Muslim representation.\n*   **Scientific Milestones:** Researchers have revealed that Neanderthals managed to survive on a \"knife\'s edge\" of environmental and social pressure for 350,000 years, providing new context to human evolutionary resilience. \n*   **Engineering Ingenuity:** For the retro-computing enthusiast, a new Raspberry Pi FireWire HAT has emerged, allowing for the modern digitization of MiniDV tapes. Meanwhile, CERN is pushing engineering boundaries with the introduction of new superconducting karts.\n*   **Consumer Corner:** Amazon’s Big Spring Sale is entering its final hours, with notable price drops on AirPods Pro 3 and various Anker charging accessories. Additionally, those seeking self-improvement can capitalize on a 65% discount on Babbel language subscriptions through April.\n*   **Space Exploration:** The countdown for Artemis II continues; the mission represents a critical step forward in the return to crewed lunar exploration.','[{\"title\": \"Claude Code Unpacked : A visual guide\", \"url\": \"https://ccunpacked.dev/\"}, {\"title\": \"CERN levels up with new superconducting karts\", \"url\": \"https://home.cern/news/