udge - Axios\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMic0FVX3lxTE1la2RZZTdoYnZBeEN3QVU5UGhRU01yVFhTc1hmdnNLeHhYRjB5XzZBc29BbndSXzlUNktDazdEV2RxaUJaWHBlU2JWaGNNN3ZjTzlWTDVRcUtfMEFpbGQ3SllCeTVsS00yM0lpbW9fWndCYm8?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Trump plans to attend Wednesday\'s Supreme Court hearing on birthright citizenship - NPR\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMilwFBVV95cUxNVEVGTXhqNW9GUERPQUVqLWdLUzRDV213aFlhejdoMk5ZMlo4Z01LN3FYRElSRDdWNm9tQy1XbEpmQmFwb3YtSzZIUmRtMERQTDF2TXZMSEEwRmk0OGZpV0NUVVJkQnppbFdfQ1RzZWtnQkNSQ3lvcjMycm8ybTl2WnZOY0kyZTNDOTRROWhINEJUODkwNUg0?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Trump issues order attempting to change rules for mail-in voting - The Washington Post\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMijgFBVV95cUxOLUNsUV9rZnJONWwwRENvNjBZdURqSElTRzdDY1FiMV9iRGpXeVVNZmtLZVo4Q3V1Ql9RZmNfS1pVdlJEam9xVU90Y3VRN05vWUs5VjRMdlVZclMyUzV4a0JJYU50S0FuREZ1NXpIR1F1cjRZRVRVWUxmVDlOQnM3b3ZpNlZRMm0xWmVXY0R3?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Kidnapping of US journalist in Iraq linked to Iranian militants - Politico\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMingFBVV95cUxNWGZzSmNwZW1wSVN1ZFRDcWlySEVRZndDU3NEV0kwMXpHNGUwR2gzemVyRFlrY2J6Z1JNd0o2b0c4ZTFValFyLXl0WHVweHlfbDM4ZmMtT2ZOWXRyRnNBaG12OWdSLWw2R29qak9pQmNweldXSHMtb3B4bU50Q2dicjgzNTRyS0ItNGliNnFFTUNMWF9MRmU5OUt5QmxKdw?oc=5\"}]','2026-04-01 09:00:29'),(28,'Daily Planet - April 02, 2026','### Global Affairs: Conflict and Geopolitics\nThe shadow of war continues to dominate the global landscape as the conflict between the United States, Israel, and Iran enters its 34th day. Amidst rising geopolitical tensions, Iran’s former foreign minister, Kharazi, was reported \"gravely wounded\" following an attack on his residence. President Trump has attempted to soothe volatile financial markets—which saw Asian stocks plunge and oil prices surge—by characterizing the conflict as \"nearing completion,\" though the administration has left significant strategic questions unanswered. As Iran marks the 47th anniversary of the Islamic Republic with defiant protests, the regional situation remains precarious, compounded by Israel’s intensified operations in Lebanon, reaching areas outside of Hezbollah’s traditional control.\n\nDomestically, the U.S. political scene remains fraught. The Supreme Court has signaled skepticism regarding President Trump’s executive order to end birthright citizenship, suggesting a potential legal roadblock for the administration. On a more optimistic note, Congressional Republican leaders have announced a framework to resolve the ongoing Homeland Security shutdown, offering a rare glimmer of legislative progress. \n\nIn other global developments, Europe is bracing for a consequential election in Hungary, a nation currently characterized by ongoing diplomatic friction as Viktor Orbán frequently leverages his veto power within the EU. Additionally, humanitarian concerns arise from Indonesia, where a 7.4 magnitude earthquake has claimed at least one life, and scientists have expressed alarm over an unprecedented, rapid snow melt-off in the American West.\n\n### Tech and Innovation: Space, AI, and Software\nSpace exploration reached a historic milestone today as NASA successfully launched the Artemis II mission. Four astronauts are currently en route to the Moon, marking a significant step in renewed lunar exploration, though the project faces ongoing legal scrutiny regarding its long-term Moon base ambitions.\n\nIn the technology sector, Anthropic has confirmed that its recent mass deletion of thousands of GitHub repositories—purportedly containing leaked source code—was an accidental overreach. Meanwhile, the AI and autonomous systems space saw a stark reminder of current limitations as Baidu’s robotaxi fleet in China was effectively paralyzed by a system-wide failure. The decentralized finance (DeFi) sector also took a hit, as the platform Drift suspended all deposits and withdrawals following a multi-million dollar security breach.\n\nOn a lighter, albeit metrics-driven note, the Linux gaming community is celebrating a win: Steam’s adoption rate on the platform has finally eclipsed the 5% threshold, signaling a maturing ecosystem for open-source gaming.\n\n### Quick Hits\n*   **Historical Echoes:** Investigators have identified the remains of a Utah teenager as a long-lost victim of serial killer Ted Bundy, providing a grim closure to a decades-old case.\n*   **Startup Watch:** The reputation of YC-backed startup Delve continues its downward spiral, while the dating app *Sonder* has paradoxically surged in popularity by implementing a deliberately cumbersome sign-up process.\n*   **Digital Hygiene:** As the web evolves in 2026, experts are debating the efficacy of current email obfuscation techniques.\n*   **Seasonal Pranks:** April Fools’ Day has arrived with its usual mix of corporate cleverness and cringeworthy marketing attempts. \n*   **Provisions:** For the budget-conscious, several promotional opportunities have emerged this month, including savings on 1Password, TurboTax, OnePlus devices, Hydrow equipment, and Lovehoney products.','[{\"title\": \"Live: Artemis II Launch Day Updates\", \"url\": \"https://www.nasa.gov/blogs/missions/2026/04/01/live-artemis-ii-launch-day-updates/\"}, {\"title\": \"Bringing Clojure programming to Enterprise (2021)\", \"url\": \"https://blogit.michelin.io/clojure-programming/\"}, {\"title\": \"Email obfuscation: What works in 2026?\", \"url\": \"https://spencermortensen.com/articles/email-obfuscation/\"}, {\"title\": \"Steam on Linux Use Skyrocketed Above 5% in March\", \"url\": \"https://www.phoronix.com/news/Steam-On-Linux-Tops-5p\"}, {\"title\": \"Quantum computing bombshells that are not April Fools\", \"url\": \"https://scottaaronson.blog/?p=9665\"}, {\"title\": \"De-fi platform Drift suspends deposits and withdrawals after millions in crypto stolen in hack\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/01/de-fi-platform-drift-suspends-deposits-and-withdraw