, {\"title\": \"Artemis II Completes First Day of Its NASA Lunar Mission - nytimes.com\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMigAFBVV95cUxQMDNzTThMLXVfUm1WcUp0WjU5U3NCVDhTVURJVEg2ajFTNkVqck9yUWhnSEQzc0RaMTdPVktVQ0t6OW44LXdTSnB2UzlLZE9JellucUp2TlMxeXF3b2xtb0pHT2xxZVNtbXNUUGpXSVVCTjR3OTBrWjVUNmo5Y3JubQ?oc=5\"}]','2026-04-02 09:01:01'),(29,'Daily Planet - April 03, 2026','### The Daily Planet\n\n#### Global Crisis and Political Upheaval\nThe geopolitical landscape is increasingly volatile as the conflict between the United States and Iran intensifies. Following a strike that destroyed Iran’s largest bridge, President Trump has issued a stark warning that \"more is to follow,\" even as intelligence assessments suggest Tehran retains significant missile capabilities. The humanitarian toll is mounting, with reports from Iran describing widespread desperation, while in southern Lebanon, the destruction of healthcare infrastructure continues. Amidst the escalation, French President Emmanuel Macron has publicly criticized the Trump administration’s approach, urging a more measured diplomatic stance.\n\nDomestically, the administration faces significant internal friction. President Trump has removed Attorney General Pam Bondi in a move that signals further volatility within the Department of Justice, with reports also indicating the dismissal of the Army Chief of Staff by Secretary Pete Hegseth. Meanwhile, signs of fracture are appearing within the Republican party, as Senators McConnell and Tillis have formally broken with the President over the proposed withdrawal from NATO.\n\n#### Technology and Innovation\nIn the tech sphere, Google continues its aggressive push in artificial intelligence with the release of the Gemma 4 open models. Conversely, Microsoft is under scrutiny; a former Azure Core engineer has published a critical assessment detailing internal decisions that they argue have fundamentally eroded trust in the Azure platform. \n\nThe space sector remains a focal point of ambition and change. NASA’s Artemis II mission is currently on track, successfully leaving Earth’s orbit for the far side of the Moon—a mission notable for being the last to operate without direct Silicon Valley involvement. Elsewhere, Archive of Our Own (AO3) has finally exited beta after 17 years, and OpenAI has expanded its media footprint by acquiring the founder-led business talk show, TBPN.\n\n#### Quick Hits\n*   **Market Pressures:** Amazon has implemented a new ‘fuel surcharge’ for sellers in direct response to the energy market instability caused by the Iran conflict.\n*   **Security Alerts:** The telehealth giant Hims & Hers has confirmed a data breach within its customer support systems, while users of the note-taking app Granola are being advised that their notes are visible via link by default.\n*   **Corporate & Cultural Shifts:** Reddit is officially moving on from *r/all*, signaling a change in its discovery architecture. Meanwhile, venture capital firm Gateway Capital has secured $25 million for its second fund.\n*   **Sports Update:** In high-stakes competition, Manchester City and Liverpool are set for an intense FA Cup quarterfinal, while the Lakers are reeling from a heavy defeat to the Thunder and a significant injury to Luka Dončić.\n*   **Consumer Savings:** Readers seeking to mitigate rising costs can currently access various promotional codes for services including DoorDash, HelloFresh, Booking.com, Chewy, and Home Depot.','[{\"title\": \"Google releases Gemma 4 open models\", \"url\": \"https://deepmind.google/models/gemma/gemma-4/\"}, {\"title\": \"Decisions that eroded trust in Azure \\u2013 by a former Azure Core engineer\", \"url\": \"https://isolveproblems.substack.com/p/how-microsoft-vaporized-a-trillion\"}, {\"title\": \"The True Shape of Io\'s Steeple Mountain\", \"url\": \"https://www.weareinquisitive.com/news/hidden-in-the-shadow\"}, {\"title\": \"ESP32-S31: 320MHz 2C RV32IMAFCP+CLIC, 512KB SRAM, GbE, 80