\"Exclusive: US intelligence assesses Iran maintains significant missile launching capability, sources say - CNN\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMihgFBVV95cUxOTjQ4eVF0c1VLSnRmd0p3ZFEwOEEyVW10X0RtUnhhWWQ0NTVTOVRrZmN6TEoyZV9PVVFoUUtCUEpyTWJ3cEFQc1ZyUlkyZ1Q0eFYtcGJnR0doMHVHZjg0LVdoalRRT3JJSTJnVURSeFZZY25vaXdqY0lUOTZZaURGUzFyajZpUQ?oc=5\"}]','2026-04-03 09:00:37'),(30,'Daily Planet - April 04, 2026','# The Daily Planet\n\n### Global Perspectives & Current Events\nThe world remains in a state of high tension as we reach day 36 of the US-Israeli strikes, with ongoing volatility in the Strait of Hormuz and a search operation underway for a US crew member downed in the region. Amidst this geopolitical friction, the humanitarian toll is stark: Iran has executed two members of a banned opposition group, while a tragic earthquake in Afghanistan has claimed the lives of eight members of a single family. Meanwhile, in the political sphere, Viktor Orban’s sixteen-year grip on power in Hungary is facing unprecedented scrutiny, and in Burkina Faso, the military leadership has formally signaled a definitive departure from democratic governance.\n\nOn a lighter note of human achievement, the NASA Artemis II crew has reached the midpoint of their lunar journey, capturing \"spectacular\" imagery of Earth that serves as a necessary, quiet reminder of our shared home in the midst of global turbulence.\n\n### Tech, Innovation, & The Markets\nThe tech landscape is shifting rapidly this week, dominated by major executive shake-ups and corporate consolidation. OpenAI is navigating an internal transition, with COO Brad Lightcap stepping into a new role for \"special projects,\" while the organization’s AGI lead has taken a leave of absence—a development mirrored by the medical leave of executive Fidji Simo. \n\nThe battle for AI dominance continues to intensify; Anthropic is seeing significant private market interest, though SpaceX looms as a potential disruptor in the investment arena. Simultaneously, Anthropic has drawn criticism for effectively barring OpenClaw from its Claude ecosystem by imposing additional subscription fees. Cybersecurity remains a critical vulnerability, as Meta has paused its partnership with Mercor following a data breach that risked exposing sensitive industry secrets. \n\nHardware consumers are feeling the pinch as well: the Lenovo Legion Go 2 has seen a sudden $650 price increase, purportedly driven by widespread supply constraints in the RAM market, while Lucid Motors is reporting a dip in Q1 sales attributed to logistics failures at a seat supplier.\n\n### Quick Hits\n*   **Workforce Shifts:** Reports indicate that Tesla’s Texas factory workforce contracted by 22% throughout 2025.\n*   **Scientific Breakthroughs:** Food science researchers have reportedly achieved a breakthrough in French fry production, potentially altering standard culinary processing.\n*   **Digital Frontiers:** An anonymous social media application is testing the viability of its platform within the unique regulatory environment of Saudi Arabia.\n*   **Consumer Corner:** While appliance deals at Maytag and a $50 discount on the iPad A16 offer some relief, Anker’s Nebula P1 projector has emerged as a high-performance favorite for portable audio enthusiasts.\n*   **Domestic News:** Brush fires are currently active near Moreno Valley and the Acton area in California, while the White House budget proposal remains notably silent on potential civilian federal pay raises.','[{\"title\": \"Tell HN: Anthropic no longer allowing Claude Code subscriptions to use OpenClaw\", \"url\": \"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47633396\"}, {\"title\": \"Artemis II crew take \\u201cspectacular\\u201d image of Earth\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/ce8jzr423p9o\"}, {\"title\": \"Emotion concepts and their function in a large language model\", \"url\": \"https://www.anthropic.com/research/emotion-concepts-function\"}, {\"title\": \"iNaturalist\", \"url\": \"https://www.inaturalist.org/\"}, {\"title\": \"Delve removed from Y Combinator\", \"url\": \"https://www.ycombinator.com/companies/delve\"}, {\"title\": \"Anthropic is having a moment in the private markets; SpaceX could spoil the party\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/03/anthropic-is-having-a-moment-in-the-private-markets-spacex-could-spoil-the-party/\"}, {\"title\": \"Lucid blames dip in Q1 sales on seat supplier issue\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/03/lucid-blames-dip-in-q1-sales-on-seat-supplier-issue/\"}, {\"title\": \"The anonymous social app that thinks it can work in Saudi Arabia\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/03/the-anonymous-social-app-that-thinks-it-can-work-in-saudi-arabia/\"}, {\"title\": \"Tesla\\u2019s Texas factory workforce reportedly shrunk 22% in 2025\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/03/teslas-texas-factory-workforce-reportedly-shrunk-22-in-2025/\"}, {\"title\": \"OpenAI executive shuffle includes new role for COO Brad Lightcap to lead \\u2018special projects\\u2019\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/03/openai-executive-shuffle-new-roles-coo-brad-lightcap-fidji-simo-kate-rouch/\"}, {\"title\": \"Anker\\u2019s Nebula P1 projector is the portable sound king\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/reviews/906455/anker-nebula-p1-review-vanlife-sound-champ\"}, {\"title\": \"Anthropic essentially bans OpenClaw from Claude by making subscribers pay extra\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/ai-artificial-intelligence/907074/anthropic-openclaw-claude-subscription-ban\"}, {\"title\": \"NASA did eventually solve Artemis II&#8217;s Outlook glitch\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/science/906988/nasa-artemis-ii-microsoft-outlook-issue-fixed\"}, {\"title\": \"OpenAI\\u2019s AGI boss is taking a leave of absence\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/ai-artificial-intelligence/906965/openais-agi-boss-is-taking-a-leave-of-absence\"}, {\"title\": \"Lenovo Legion Go 2 suddenl