al silent on civilian federal pay raise - Federal News Network\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMisAFBVV95cUxORXV3cmhFRFM5TVY5UTY2R2VzQk5wLUVvY3EtaUxBSnRyX2pMU2pTbDEtMzVIU2ZfRmtzNEpKWW9IRkowUjBicGoxQ3FBTkVpZUE5YXVTY2RWaEJ3YXhsTjhBN1NnRkZrRjRldmhVV3Vxd0I5clFnMEN6WnotV1M3N0doeU1PRzlxYUdNdDR0T1d5WVUwel9qVW9sYWVIdUdqb190alpIOFRyZkNSb2FDeg?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"NASA\'s Artemis II crew are quite the photographers. See what they\'ve snapped so far - npr.org\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMimAFBVV95cUxNaFlLYklEWFEzRTg3N19LamlrN285Y0Z0MGFyQ0wxUFJGS0hlTWowQzdwMlplZ1hCQ2FoUXU1OEhSc2VZRXhWZFVSSDlEWDJ6bXdYSVJyb3BLVUxZNDFDc1djRjBDWVcxa1B4LXNvX29PZGtNWmQwRTBtSk5QeUhIT0pNaXZEUXJnbWZicXV4RUZKRGlNSFpVTg?oc=5\"}]','2026-04-04 09:00:13'),(31,'Daily Planet - April 26, 2026','### Global Briefing: Escalating Tensions and Domestic Turbulence\n\nThe geopolitical landscape remains acutely volatile following the shooting at the White House Correspondents’ Dinner. Authorities have confirmed that the suspect intentionally targeted Trump administration officials, an event that has predictably ignited a firestorm of conspiracy theories and deepened domestic polarization. Amid this, the international theater offers little respite: Prime Minister Netanyahu has ordered a \"vigorous\" military escalation against Hezbollah in Lebanon, while in Mali, the defense minister was killed during a surge of rebel activity. Furthermore, diplomatic channels are fraying, with the U.S. canceling envoy talks with Pakistan regarding the Iran conflict, even as Iranian officials head to Russia for high-level discussions. In Colombia, a tragic highway bombing claimed 19 lives, casting a grim shadow over upcoming national elections.\n\n### Technology and Innovation: The Architecture of Power\n\nThe intersection of technology and political influence continues to dominate the discourse. Reports detail how Amazon is aggressively pivoting its podcast strategy toward total monetization, signaling a shift in how platforms leverage creator content. In the mobility sector, Elon Musk has made a significant admission regarding his vision, while the broader tech industry observes the enduring legacy of Tim Cook’s leadership. Meanwhile, the cultural cachet of the \"tech elite\" is increasingly literal; in the Bay Area, the bar for entry into high-end real estate has risen to include Anthropic equity. On the research front, a fascinating experiment in \"biological-style\" AI memory, utilizing decay-based recall, highlights the ongoing race to imbue silicon with human-like cognitive limitations.\n\n### Quick Hits\n\n*   **Athletic Prowess:** History was made as Sawe became the first athlete to complete a sub-two-hour marathon in a competitive race.\n*   **Infrastructure & Security:** A newly uncovered intelligence report describes \"Fast16,\" a sophisticated software sabotage operation discovered five years prior to the Stuxnet attack.\n*   **Environmental Concerns:** North America’s butterfly populations, specifically the Western Monarch, are facing a dramatic and concerning decline.\n*   **Cultural & Consumer Notes:**\n    *   **Internet Nostalgia:** A digital enthusiast has purchased the rights to Friendster for $30,000, promising a revival project.\n    *   **The Desktop Wars:** The exodus from Windows to Linux continues to gain anecdotal traction, with users reporting little desire to return.\n    *   **Retail Spotlight:** Ikea is courting pet owners with a new inflatable chair specifically \"tested by cats,\" while smart-home enthusiasts are flocking to premium bird feeders and permanent outdoor lighting solutions from Govee and Eufy.\n    *   **Arts & Entertainment:** Tomora’s *Come Closer* has emerged as a critical darling, praised as an evocative love letter to the 90s dance era.','[{\"title\": \"I bought Friendster for $30k \\u2013 Here\'s what I\'m doing with it\", \"url\": \"https://ca98am79.medium.com/i-bought-friendster-for-30k-heres-what-i-m-doing-with-it-d5e8ddb3991d\"}, {\"title\": \"Fast16: High-precision software sabotage 5 years before Stuxnet\", \"url\": \"https://www.sentinelone.com/labs/fast16-mystery-shadowbrokers-reference-reveals-high-precision-software-sabotage-5-years-before-stuxnet/\"}, {\"title\": \"Sawe becomes first athlete to run a sub-two-hour marathon in a competitive race\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/sport/athletics/articles/crm1m7e0zwzo\"}, {\"title\": \"Butterflies are in decline across North America, a look at the Western Monarch\", \"url\": \"https://www.smithsonianmag.com/science-nature/butterflies-are-in-dramatic-decline-across-north-america-a-close-look-at-the-western-monarch-shows-why-180988582/\"}, {\"title\": \"Show HN: AI memory with biological decay (52% recall)\", \"url\": \"https://github.com/sachitrafa/YourMemory\"}, {\"title\": \"The Stanford freshmen who want to rule the world . . . will probably read this book and try even harder\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/26/the-stanford-freshmen-who-want-to-rule-the-world-will-probably-read-this-book-and-try-even-harder/\"}, {\"title\": \"Amazon\\u2019s new podcast strategy: Monetize everything\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/26/amazons-new-podcast-strategy-monetize-everything/\"}, {\"title\": \"What Tim Cook built\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/26/what-tim-cook-built/\"}, {\"title\": \"TechCrunch Mobility: Elon\\u2019s admission\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/26/techcrunch-mobility-elons-admission/\"}, {\"title\": \"To buy this Bay Area home, you\\u2019ll need Anthropic equity\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/26/to-buy-this-bay-area-home-youll-need-anthropic-equity/\"}, {\"title\": \"Google\\u2019s new gradient icon design is coming to more apps\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/918852/googles-new-gradient-icon-design-is-coming-to-more-apps\"}, {\"title\": \"Trump turns the WHCD shooting into a pitch for the White House ballroom\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/policy/918843/trump-whcd-attack-white-house-ballroom\"}, {\"title\": \"Tomora\\u2019s Come Closer is an ecstatic love letter to 90s dance music\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/entertainment/918826/tomora-come-closer-review-90s-dance-music\"}, {\"title\": \"Skylight\\u2019s 15-inch smart calendar is down to its lowest price to date\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/gadgets/918544/skylight-15-inch-smart-calendar-2-mothers-day-deal-2026-sale\"}, {\"title\": \"After three months on Linux, I don\\u2019t miss Windows at all\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/918797/switched-to-linux-dont-miss-windows\"}, {\"title\": \"\\u2018STAGED\\u2019: Conspiracy Theories Are Everywhere Following White House Correspondents\\u2019 Dinner Shooting\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/staged-conspiracy-theories-are-everywhere-following-white-house-correspondents-dinner-shooting/\"}, {\"title\": \"The Best Kindle Accessories (2026): Cases, Page Turners, Stickers\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/best-kindle-accessories/\"}, {\"title\": \"The Smart Bird Feeders Everyone\\u2019s Talking About (and Actually Buying) (2026)\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/best-smart-bird-feeders/\"}, {\"title\": \"The Best Permanent Outdoor Lights (2026): Govee, Eufy, Cync\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/should-you-get-permanent-outdoor-lights/\"}, {\"title\": \"Ikea\'s New Blow-Up Chair Was Tested by Cats\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/ikea-new-blow-up-chair-was-tested-by-cats/\"}, {\"title\": \"Trump and officials \'likely\' targets of press dinner shooting suspect, authorities believe\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c2d8dg57rzdo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"I was in the room with Trump and heard the low thudding sound of gunfire\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c62j23wzeqeo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Trump cancels US envoys\' trip to Pakistan fo