lTzF5S3FSbUxYTE5PRVIzYWFCU1E?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Chicago Police Officer Killed In Swedish Hospital Shooting Identified As John Bartholomew - Block Club Chicago\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMiygFBVV95cUxQOHp5Wm5RUWNiMHRBTjlnclRBNWhGZGRUckhGblU0TXBSVVJtQ0JHZmp3WWJ6dmF4Ui1ZZU9TSThEd00tYjAzVWs4alNZdmQ2VEF0SEk4VFE4M2xDS2F6UzJHdmowcXVZQ1U3WjdueUxsUkV3Q3g0Z2Rrc3JMSHlrRm9OS2pxQ0JJcnVtVjJjajlNMG1RVWZLZy1SWW85cmlqNGlBX2gtM0hiVnhLOFNOZXp5RUd4OW41UVJhM0pMNmVLVHpQeG94LURB?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"King Charles U.S. visit comes at tense moment in transatlantic relationship - NPR\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMidkFVX3lxTFB2MDBzWkVfaGpVU1dMakstT2VJRUlzall0YW9mcTd1MFp1c3FhSi1GRDdiTGlkTXRYWjV0NVh6eU9TRGp1TG1IT2xYamFuQnNHQWZwR2NsWWNyYjBzTkg0eTVIellTUFhJWkEzbTBLMkZNSHBIQXc?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"US-Iran conflict: What\\u2019s the latest as the Islamabad talks stall? - Al Jazeera\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Powerful Storm Sweeps Across Texas and Kills 2, Displacing Dozens - The New York Times\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMiiwFBVV95cUxQVW8wYWc1V0Q4Nnl3bzFBM3R0eGR1NllGQmR5c0ZUc1VrVG41OENNTWxfeXRhZWlDOGhKRHJDUWFqYk1kMzBLWW1JU0Z5ZjduMnNXZTdXOHcyVVl0ZmE0WC1QSktNdEU5VWhLeDBrWl9vSEpCUlk0bUNVTlVDenRzcGxEOVI0WmtOQjZz?oc=5\"}]','2026-04-26 22:55:24'),(32,'Daily Planet - April 27, 2026','### Global Update: Tensions and Tragedies\n\nThe world remains gripped by the dual crises of the Iran war and the aftermath of the White House Correspondents’ Dinner (WHCD) shooting. As the conflict in Iran enters its 59th day, diplomatic efforts to stem the tide are intensifying; the Iranian foreign minister is currently in Russia for high-level talks with Vladimir Putin, while oil prices have ticked upward in response to stalled peace negotiations. Simultaneously, the environmental toll of the conflict is becoming increasingly visible. Elsewhere, regional instability continues to escalate, with maritime threats rising as pirates seize vessels off the Somali coast, and North Korea intensifying its involvement in Ukraine, marked by Kim Jong Un’s inauguration of a memorial for soldiers lost in the war. \n\nDomestically, the investigation into the WHCD shooting remains charged with political friction. The 31-year-old suspect, who identified himself as a \"friendly federal assassin,\" has become the focal point of a volatile media environment, with Donald Trump vocally rejecting conspiracy theories—some suggesting the event was staged—while simultaneously engaging in heated clashes with the press regarding his manifesto. In the humanitarian sphere, the situation in Darfur remains dire, as war and a lack of infrastructure drive a lethal measles epidemic.\n\n### Tech and Innovation: Reframing the Future\n\nThe tech landscape is shifting from rapid growth to a focus on sustainability and human-centric design. Truecaller is finding that market maturation brings new pressures, signaling a broader industry shift toward consolidation rather than blind expansion. In the Amazon ecosystem, a new, aggressive monetization strategy for podcasts suggests the company is looking to extract maximum value from its existing media footprint, while reflections on Tim Cook’s tenure remind us that the era of \"building\" is often defined by steady, incremental dominance.\n\nMeanwhile, the dialogue around Artificial Intelligence is maturing. A growing chorus of thought leaders is cautioning that AI should function as a tool to elevate and challenge our cognitive processes, rather than serve as a replacement for human intellect. This sentiment echoes in the maker community, where there is a burgeoning permission to let go of stalled side projects, emphasizing that creativity is often better served by knowing when to move on rather than forcing a project to completion.\n\n### Quick Hits\n\n*   **Culture & Lifestyle:** For those seeking analog comfort in a digital age, the 2026 Kindle accessory market—ranging from page turners to stickers—is thriving. Meanwhile, smart home enthusiasts are turning to \"permanent\" outdoor lighting solutions and high-end smart bird feeders.\n*   **Entertainment:** Music aficionados should look to Tomora’s *Come Closer*, a record that serves as an ecstatic, modern homage to the dance floors of the 90s.\n*   **Computing:** The \"Linux-curious\" may find encouragement in recent user reports suggesting that the transition from Windows is smoother than ever, with many finding little reason to return to the legacy OS.\n*   **Sports:** A significant blow to the Netherlands’ World Cup 2026 prospects, as a season-ending ACL injury sidelines Xavi Simons.\n*   **Humanities:** A poignant reminder of the value of history comes from Mauritania, where a lone guardian continues his dedicated efforts to preserve rare Islamic texts against the pressures of time and neglect.','[{\"title\": \"It\'s OK to abandon your side-project\", \"url\": \"https://robbowen.digital/wrote-about/abandoned-side-projects/\"}, {\"title\": \"Flipdiscs\", \"url\": \"https://flipdisc.io\"}, {\"title\": \"I bought Friendster for $30k \\u2013 Here\'s what I\'m doing with it\", \"url\": \"https://ca98am79.medium.com/i-bought-friendster-for-30k-heres-what-i-m-doing-with-it-d5e8ddb3991d\"}, {\"title\": \"TurboQuant: A first-principles walkthrough\", \"url\": \"https://arkaung.github.io/interactive-turboquant/\"}, {\"title\": \"AI should elevate your thinking, not replace it\", \"url\": \"https://www.koshyjohn.com/blog/ai-should-elevate-your-thinking-not-replace-it/\"}, {\"title\": \"Truecaller faces mounting pressures as its growth matures\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/26/truecaller-faces-mounting-pressures-as-its-growth-matures/\"}, {\"title\": \"The Stanford freshmen who want to rule the world . . . will probably read this book and try even harder\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/26/the-stanford-freshmen-who-want-to-rule-the-world-will-probably-read-th