, \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMisgFBVV95cUxPaTNJaFo2TXBHZzlKbVNzTlFOdHdEZHVzTWdDLXhqdUlYTWc1MXdDMmVBRmxxV1J5dXVJWFRBX3JneW9rX2pfd21EX21lT0wxUnFDNFdqdnhOWE1mdlJQdnVzX0UwOEh1UFdVX1dNSUNiWDJLYW1STDMyaTJEVm4yaER4Z1FLWmtHYkVCbjd0YW1VNHdKZ0FEcW5QZnkxN1ZqN0ctaWpWaTFVTWZBTlhncGdn?oc=5\"}]','2026-04-27 09:01:01'),(33,'Daily Planet - April 28, 2026','### The Daily Planet | April 28, 2026\n\n#### Global Affairs: A Cycle of Volatility\nThe international landscape remains fraught with tension this morning. Security concerns in the United States have reached a fever pitch following an attempted assassination of President Trump at a Washington dinner. The incident has intensified the ongoing dialogue regarding the state of political violence in the country, which observers describe as a cycle currently operating in dangerous overdrive. Amidst this, the Trump administration finds itself embroiled in a separate, public standoff with late-night host Jimmy Kimmel, with the White House and the First Lady calling for his dismissal following a controversial joke—a demand Kimmel has firmly rejected.\n\nElsewhere, the global geopolitical map remains unstable. In the Middle East, Israel has tightened its security grip under the cover of a tenuous ceasefire, while Hezbollah continues to assert its operational power. Simultaneously, President Trump is weighing a proposal from Iran concerning the reopening of the Strait of Hormuz—a strategic artery currently being tested by the movement of a Russian superyacht through the blockade. Meanwhile, a different kind of threat has been addressed in Europe, where an Austrian national has been put on trial for plotting an attack on a Taylor Swift concert. On a lighter diplomatic note, King Charles and Queen Camilla have officially commenced their state visit to the United States.\n\n#### The AI Reconfiguration\nThe technological landscape is undergoing a structural shift, most notably in the collapse of the foundational alliance between Microsoft and OpenAI. The two organizations are ending their exclusive revenue-sharing agreement, a move that follows the resolution of legal friction surrounding OpenAI’s $50 billion Amazon deal. \n\nThe industry’s obsession with artificial intelligence continues to permeate every vertical:\n*   **Enterprise Integration:** The venerable Bloomberg Terminal is slated for an \"AI makeover,\" signaling that even the most traditional financial bastions are folding to the trend. \n*   **Creative Workflow:** Logitech is attempting to bridge the gap between AI and productivity with its new MX Creative Console, now offering plugins for Microsoft Office.\n*   **Platform Shifts:** Google is testing AI-driven chatbot search functionality for YouTube, while Canonical has outlined a comprehensive strategy to weave AI features directly into the Ubuntu Linux ecosystem. \n\nLegal scrutiny of the industry\'s leaders remains high, evidenced by the ongoing, contentious jury selection in the *Musk v. Altman* trial, where early reports suggest a deeply unfavorable public sentiment toward Elon Musk.\n\n#### Quick Hits\n*   **Economy & Markets:** India’s on-demand home services sector is surging, underscored by Snabbit’s successful $56 million funding round. \n*   **Digital Risks:** The FTC warns that consumer losses to social media-based scams have reached a staggering $2.1 billion.\n*   **Media Industry:** Speculation is mounting regarding the potential sale of Letterboxd, the cherished social hub for film enthusiasts.\n*   **Innovation & Lifestyle:** High-end, boutique branding reaches the pet aisle with the launch of \"Drizzle on Top,\" a dog food line positioned for the ultra-wealthy. Meanwhile, Adidas has secured a performance milestone, as their record-light footwear powered the first sub-2-hour marathon.\n*   **Archive:** For those inclined toward historical curiosities, *Talkie* has surfaced—a fascinating 13B vintage language model modeled on 1930s speech patterns.\n*   **Astronomy:** NASA’s *Astronomy Picture of the Day* invites the public to test their observational skills with a challenge to locate a currently visible comet.','[{\"title\": \"GTFOBins\", \"url\": \"https://gtfobins.org/\"}, {\"title\": \"Talkie: a 13B vintage language model from 1930\", \"url\": \"https://talkie-lm.com/introducing-talkie\"}, {\"title\": \"Microsoft and OpenAI end their exclusive and revenue-sharing deal\", \"url\": \"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-27/microsoft-to-stop-sharing-revenue-with-main-ai-partner-openai\"}, {\"title\": \"Is my blue your blue?\", \"url\": \"https://ismy.blue/\"}, {\"title\": \"Can You Find the Comet?\", \"url\": \"https://apod.nasa.gov/apod/ap260427.html\"}, {\"title\": \"Drizzle on top: a new high-end dog food brand is coming for the 1%\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/27/drizzle-on-top-a-new-high-end-dog-food-brand-is-coming-for-the-1/\"}, {\"title\": \"India\\u2019s Snabbit closes $56M round as investor interest in on-demand home services heats up\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/27/indias-snabbit-closes-56m-round-as-investor-interest-heats-up-in-on-demand-home-services/\"}, {\"title\": \"Letterboxd, the social platform for film buffs, reportedly looking for new owner\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/27/letterboxd-sale-film-social-media-semafor-versant-ankler/\"}, {\"title\": \"Consumers lost $2.1B to social media scams in 2025, FTC reports\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/27/consumers-lost-2-1-billion-to-social-media-scams-in-2025-ftc-reports/\"}, {\"title\": \"OpenAI ends Microsoft legal peril over its $50B Amazon deal\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/27/openai-ends-microsoft-legal-peril-over-its-50b-amazon-deal/\"}, {\"title\": \"Microsoft Office can now be controlled with Logitech\\u2019s MX Creative Console\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/919165/logitech-mx-ecosystem-creative-console-productivity-plugins-microsoft-office-slack-notion\"}, {\"title\": \"Jury selection in Musk v. Altman: \\u2018People don\\u2019t like him\\u2019\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/919469/elon-musk-dont-like\"}, {\"title\": \"Google is testing AI chatbot search for YouTube\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/streaming/919441/google-ask-youtube-ai-chatbot-search\"}, {\"title\": \"Canonical lays out a plan for AI in Ubuntu Linux\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/919411/canonical-ubuntu-linux-ai-features\"}, {\"title\": \"Trump demands ABC fire Jimmy Kimmel\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/policy/919337/president-trump-jimmy-kimmel-fire-abc\"}, {\"title\": \"The Bloomberg Terminal Is Getting an AI Makeover, Like It or Not\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/the-bloomberg-terminal-is-getting-an-ai-makeover-like-it-or-not/\"}, {\"title\": \"Adidas\\u2019 Lightest Shoes Ever Were Behind the First Sub-2-Hour Marathon\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/sub-2-hour-marathon-adidas-shoes-sabastian-sawe/\"}, {\"title\": \"Best Buy Discount Codes: Up to 60% Off\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/best-buy-discount-code/\"}, {\"title\": \"OnePlus Promo Code: $70 Off | April 2026\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/oneplus-promo-code/\"}, {\"title\": \"Hulu Promo Codes & Discounts: 20% Off in April\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/hulu-promo-code/\"}, {\"title\": \"Suspect charged with attempted assassination of Trump at Washington dinner\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cew7wez72vxo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"US political violence generates a familiar cycle - this time it\'s in overdrive\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cje4eeyq27lo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Jimmy Kimmel rejects White House criticism over Melania widow joke\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c04x40d4424o?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Russian superyacht sails through Strait of Hormuz despite blockade\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cm2pn8zdxdjo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Austrian goes on trial accused of plotting attack on Taylor Swift concert\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c05d5qgprjzo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Palestine weekly wrap: Under cover of ceasefire, Israel increases grip\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/4/28/palestine-weekly-wrap-under-cover-of-ceasefire-israel-increases-grip?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Down but not out: In war with Israel, Hezbollah shows it is still powerful\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/features/2026/4/28/down-but-not-out-in-war-with-israel-hezbollah-shows-it-is-still-powerful?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"\\u2018Should be fired\\u2019: Why the Trumps want Jimmy Kimmel sacked\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/4/28/should-be-fired-why-the-trumps-want-jimmy-kimmel-sacked?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Trump reviews Iranian proposal aimed at reopening Strait of Hormuz\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/4/28/trump-reviews-iranian-proposal-aimed-at-reopening-strait-of-hormuz?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Athletics great Allyson Felix aiming to compete at 2028 Los Angeles Games\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2026/4/28/athletics-great-allyson-felix-aiming-to-compete-at-2028-los-angeles-games?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Trump wants a correspondents\\u2019 dinner redo. Critics aren\\u2019t convinced. - The Washington Post\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMiiwFBVV95cUxPQ2laUm1JTmFpdWU0dGE3VWw3QXdnaXRCdnMtcmNzeUpIQ2ZTQ2hzcDFnbEFkbDlGWUpZOExxa01HQmYzQjlXaGhxcUk4Q3NRdk9yTkRnVUFTV3ZKaUtEM296TV9aeUJoOHgyTzBvQU55R0RRdU9xZVk4SmpidXE0RzNINXVCbW9XMDZN?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Trump Skeptical of Iran\\u2019s Strait of Hormuz Proposal - WSJ\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Kimmel Pushes Back Against White House And FLOTUS Criticism Of \\u2018Expectant Widow\\u2019 Joke - Forbes\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"In pictures: King Charles and Queen Camilla begin US state visit - BBC\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMiWkFVX3lxTFBaNmpSQmp1ZWdkQ01UVnF0Z29uenBsUVoyMnN2WGdfQUUwc29FS2lKTV9tREhyY1U5Vm1yY2J2eFlaMEZWSlJaWHJIak9QUlNJN3ZJaEpmcTNWUQ?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Mexico\\u2019s Sheinbaum rules out a conflict with US over 2 CIA agents killed in Chihuahua accident - Politico\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.?oc=5\"}]','2026-04-28 09:00:28'),(34,'Daily Planet - April 29, 2026','### Global Affairs & Geopolitical Shifts\n\nThe international landscape remains dominated by the escalating confrontation between the United States and Iran. Following reports of a deadly school attack, the Pentagon faces intensifying scrutiny over its silence, while the White House, under President Trump, has signaled an intent to prepare for an extended blockade of Iran. This geopolitical fracture is reverberating globally; the UAE’s departure from OPEC marks a significant disruption to oil market stability, and nations like India are left assessing the viability of strategic infrastructure projects, such as the Chabahar port, amidst the worsening conflict.\n\nMeanwhile, a peculiar and high-stakes legal drama is unfolding stateside: former FBI Director James Comey has been indicted, reportedly stemming from an Instagram post involving a seashell photo deemed a threat against President Trump. This occurs against the backdrop of an ongoing investigation into a recent attempt on the President’s life—a case that continues to baffle authorities given the suspect’s lack of a clear radical footprint. \n\nIn other global developments, King Charles III has delivered a historic address to the U.S. Congress, using the platform to urge for greater checks on executive power—a notable diplomatic signal as he hosts the current administration. Elsewhere, environmental markers show a rare glimmer of hope: global rainforest loss slowed in 2025 following a record-breaking year of destruction, providing a solitary positive headline in an otherwise volatile news cycle.\n\n### Tech, Innovation & The OpenAI Trial\n\nThe tech sector is currently defined by the unfolding courtroom saga between Elon Musk and Sam Altman. As the trial proceeds, the proceedings have increasingly morphed into a relitigation of the duo’s former friendship. Musk, in his testimony, characterized his founding involvement in OpenAI as a defensive maneuver to prevent a \"Terminator outcome,\" though observers note his performance has at times appeared more performative than substantive. \n\nAs the legal theater plays out, commercial integration continues unabated. Amazon has begun rolling out new OpenAI products across its AWS ecosystem and is simultaneously deploying an AI-powered audio Q&A feature on its product pages. Yet, the friction between AI giants and creative industries is hardening; Taylor Swift is aggressively escalating legal action against AI copycats, signaling a growing industry-wide movement to protect intellectual property from generative models. \n\nLabor unrest also lingers beneath the surface of the AI boom, with reports that hundreds of workers tasked with training Meta’s models face potential layoffs—a stark reminder of the \"undignified\" human costs associated with the rapid industrialization of artificial intelligence.\n\n### Quick Hits\n\n*   **Platform Shifts:** Ghostty is departing the GitHub ecosystem, and HardenedBSD has officially moved its operations to the decentralized platform Radicle.\n*   **Controversy in Tech:** Match Group has invested $100 million into the cruising app *Sniffies*, sparking internal anxiety among the app’s user base regarding the potential \"straightification\" of the platform.\n*   **Media & Discourse:** Conspiracy theorist creators are seeing a surge in viewership, with the White House Correspondents\' Dinner serving as a flashpoint for disinformation narratives.\n*   **Sports:** FIFA has introduced a \"red card\" penalty for players covering their mouths during World Cup matches, an attempt to curb private communication during play.\n*   **Developer Insight:** For those following the Rust ecosystem, a new critique highlights the specific classes of bugs that the language’s safety guarantees still fail to catch.','[{\"title\": \"Ghostty is leaving GitHub\", \"url\": \"https://mitchellh.com/writing/ghostty-leaving-github\"}, {\"title\": \"Bugs Rust won\'t catch\", \"url\": \"https://corrode.dev/blog/bugs-rust-wont-catch/\"}, {\"title\": \"HardenedBSD Is Now Officially on Radicle\", \"url\": \"https://hardenedbsd.org/article/shawn-webb/2026-04-26/hardenedbsd-officially-radicle\"}, {\"title\": \"Tell HN: An update from the new Tindie team\", \"url\": \"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47945522\"}, {\"title\": \"How ChatGPT serves ads\", \"url\": \"https://www.buchodi.com/how-chatgpt-serves-ads-heres-the-full-attribution-loop/\"}, {\"title\": \"How one venture firm is investing in an increasingly fragmented world\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/28/how-one-venture-firm-is-navigating-an-increasingly-fragmented-world/\"}, {\"title\": \"At his OpenAI trial, Musk relitigates an old friendship\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/28/at-his-openai-trial-musk-relitigates-an-old-friendship/\"}, {\"title\": \"Amazon is already offering new OpenAI products on AWS\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/28/amazon-is-already-offering-new-openai-products-on-aws/\"}, {\"title\": \"Amazon launches an AI-powered audio Q&A experience on product pages\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/28/amazon-launches-an-ai-powered-audio-qa-experience-on-product-pages/\"}, {\"title\": \"Match Group invests $100M in Sniffies, a cruising app for gay men\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/28/match-group-invests-100-million-in-sniffies-a-cruising-app-for-gay-men/\"}, {\"title\":