new strategic options. As traffic through the Strait of Hormuz remains stalled, the U.S. is actively lobbying for a new international coalition to secure maritime transit. Meanwhile, diplomatic tensions are high, evidenced by Hegseth’s ongoing clashes with lawmakers regarding the conflict and Pakistan’s move to open alternative land trade routes into Iran.\n\nDomestically, the political climate remains volatile. Former FBI Director James Comey has surrendered following charges related to threatening the President’s life via social media, and Louisiana\'s gubernatorial office is navigating a potential suspension of House primaries following a contentious court ruling. Amidst this friction, a moment of tradition: President Trump and the First Lady welcomed King Charles III and Queen Camilla to the White House for a state visit commemorating 250 years of shared heritage.\n\n### Tech & Innovation: The Trillion-Dollar Horizon\n\nThe scale of capital flowing into artificial intelligence continues to defy gravity. Sources indicate that Anthropic is preparing a massive $50 billion funding round that could value the company at an eye-watering $900 billion. This coincides with a broader shift in industrial infrastructure: SoftBank is pivoting toward the construction of robotics-integrated data centers, with reports suggesting they are already eyeing a $100 billion IPO for the venture.\n\nWhile cloud business remains the primary engine for tech giants—Amazon’s capital spending is surging to accommodate massive growth—the picture is more nuanced for legacy players. Microsoft reported a decline in Xbox revenue, contrasting with its cloud success, while Google continues to see record-breaking search volume. The legal scrutiny of industry titans is also intensifying: Elon Musk finds himself in a precarious position, as his own social media history is being used against him in court, while a coalition including Amazon and Meta is moving to challenge the dominant duopoly of Google Pay and PhonePe in the Indian market.\n\n### Quick Hits\n\n*   **Science & Culture:** The scientific community is mourning the loss of J. Craig Venter, the genomics pioneer who passed away at 79. In a lighter cultural note, the White House Correspondents\' Dinner party circuit saw a surprising winner in the form of Grindr, which dominated the evening’s discourse.\n*   **Developments & Discontent:** The \"Looksmaxxing\" subculture has spilled into the legal sphere, with Alorah Ziva suing for alleged battery. Meanwhile, first responders have expressed mounting concerns regarding the worsening safety performance of Waymo autonomous vehicles.\n*   **Industry Tools:** The Zig project has publicly clarified its rationale for an anti-AI contribution policy, sparking debate in developer circles. On a more practical note for engineers, Noctua has officially released its 3D CAD models, and the developers of the high-performance editor Zed have officially hit their 1.0 release.\n*   **Global Briefs:** Myanmar has reduced the prison sentence of Aung San Suu Kyi, and the Christchurch mass shooter has failed in his appeal to overturn his conviction. In sports, a high-tension brawl triggered by a punch has resulted in a 13-game ban for a Zaragoza goalkeeper, while the NBA playoffs continue as the Rockets forced a Game 6 against the Lakers.','[{\"title\": \"Where the goblins came from\", \"url\": \"https://openai.com/index/where-the-goblins-came-from/\"}, {\"title\": \"Noctua releases official 3D CAD models for its cooling fans\", \"url\": \"https://www.noctua.at/en/3d-cad-models\"}, {\"title\": \"Zed 1.0\", \"url\": \"https://zed.dev/blog/zed-1-0\"}, {\"title\": \"The Zig project\'s rationale for their anti-AI contribution policy\", \"url\": \"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Apr/30/zig-anti-ai/\"}, {\"title\": \"Craig Venter has died\", \"url\": \"https://www.jcvi.org/media-center/j-craig-venter-genomics-pioneer-and-founder-jcvi-and-diploid-genomics-inc-dies-79\"}, {\"title\": \"SoftBank is creating a robotics company that builds data centers \\u2014 and already eyeing a $100B IPO\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/29/softbank-is-creating-a-robotics-company-that-builds-data-centers-and-already-eyeing-a-100b-ipo/\"}, {\"title\": \"Amazon, Meta join fight to end Google Pay, PhonePe dominance in India\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/29/amazon-meta-join-fight-to-end-google-pay-phonepe-dominance-in-india/\"}, {\"title\": \"Amazon\\u2019s cloud business is surging \\u2014 and so is its capital spending\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/29/amazons-cloud-business-is-surging-and-so-is-its-capital-spending/\"}, {\"title\": \"Sources: Anthropic could raise a new $50B round at a valuation of $900B\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/29/sources-anthropic-could-raise-a-new-50b-round-at-a-valuation-of-900b/\"}, {\"title\": \"On the stand, Elon Musk can\\u2019t escape his own tweets\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/29/on-the-stand-elon-musk-cant-escape-his-own-tweets/\"}, {\"title\": \"Elon Musk\\u2019s worst enemy in court is Elon Musk\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/921022/elon-musk-cross-openai-altman\"}, {\"title\": \"Grindr \\u2014 yes, Grindr \\u2014 won the WHCD party circuit\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/column/920845/grindr-whcd-party-2026\"}, {\"title\": \"Splatoon Raiders preorders for the Switch 2 are nearly 20 percent off\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/gadgets/920848/splatoon-raiders-physical-edition-preorder-switch-2-walmart-deal-sale\"}, {\"title\": \"Microsoft reports sinking Xbox revenue as its cloud business climbs\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/920785/microsoft-xbox-revenue-q3-2026-earnings\"}, {\"title\": \"Google Search queries hit an \\u2018all time high\\u2019 last quarter\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/920815/google-alphabet-q1-2026-earnings-sundar-pichai\"}, {\"title\": \"Nike Promo Codes and Deals: 30% Off\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/nike-promo-code/\"}, {\"title\": \"How Elon Musk Squeezed OpenAI: They \'Are Gonna Want to Kill Me\\u2019\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/model-behavior-elon-musk-cross-examined-sam-altman/\"}, {\"title\": \"Emergency First Responders Say Waymos Are Getting Worse\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/emergency-first-responders-say-waymos-are-getting-worse/\"}, {\"title\": \"Taylor Swift Wants to Trademark Her Likeness. These TikTok Deepfake Ads Show Why\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/taylor-swift-rihanna-tiktok-deepfake-ads/\"}, {\"title\": \"Female Looksmaxxer Alorah Ziva Is Suing Clavicular for Alleged Battery\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/female-looksmaxxer-alorah-ziva-suing-clavicular-for-alleged-battery/\"}, {\"title\": \"Oil price hits highest since 2022 after report Trump to be briefed on new Iran options\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cx21m88rd14o?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Comey surrenders over charge of threatening Trump\'s life in Instagram post\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c70vzj1nrddo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Jewish agency warned of \'high\' threat level ahead of Bondi shooting, report finds\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cdjpw0n889yo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Christchurch mass killer loses bid to overturn conviction\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cg5p6zq19npo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Three takeaways from Hegseth\'s clash with lawmakers over Iran war\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c78qd6ll8xlo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Pakistan opens up road trade routes into Iran amid Hormuz blockade\", \"url\": \"https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/4/30/pakistan-opens-up-road-trade-routes-into-iran-amid-hormuz-blockade?traffic_source=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Myanmar\\u2019s blanket prison term reduction trims Aung San