news.google.?oc=5\"}]','2026-05-02 09:00:21'),(38,'Daily Planet - May 03, 2026','### Geopolitical Volatility and Global Flashpoints\n\nThe international landscape remains dominated by the repercussions of the Iran-U.S. standoff. As fuel prices surge, the economic fallout is becoming tangible: Spirit Airlines has announced a shutdown, a stark casualty of the volatility. Meanwhile, the administration is reviewing new offers from Tehran, though skepticism remains high, with threats of further strikes looming should Iran \"misbehave.\" \n\nConcurrently, a realignment in European defense is underway; U.S. troop withdrawals from Germany—and potentially Spain and Italy—are sparking concern among high-ranking U.S. Republicans regarding the strategic signal sent to Moscow. In the Middle East, the humanitarian situation continues to deteriorate as Israel issues new forced displacement orders in southern Lebanon. Amidst these tensions, a clandestine network has emerged, smuggling Starlink technology into Iran to circumvent state-imposed internet blackouts.\n\nIn domestic news, the legal battle over reproductive healthcare has reached the Supreme Court, with drugmakers urgently petitioning to restore mail-order access to abortion medication.\n\n### Tech, Innovation, and Industry Shifts\n\nThe artificial intelligence sector is undergoing a necessary recalibration. In a significant cultural milestone, the Oscars have officially ruled AI-generated actors and scripts ineligible for competition, drawing a firm line in the creative sand. On the technical front, IBM has unveiled its Granite 4.1 model family, while the discourse around managing AI-induced complexity is intensifying—evidenced by developers advocating for YAML-based specs to combat \"AI psychosis.\"\n\nCorporate maneuvers also signal a cooling or shifting of priorities. Netflix has delayed the highly anticipated *Narnia* adaptation, helmed by Greta Gerwig, opting for a 2027 theatrical release rather than an immediate streaming premiere. In the tech graveyard, Ask.com has officially shuttered, marking the final farewell for the once-iconic Jeeves. Meanwhile, Meta faces a sobering financial reality following a historic court loss in New Mexico that threatens to balloon well beyond its initial $375 million penalty.\n\n### Quick Hits: The Pulse of the Week\n\n*   **Sports & Culture:** Gretchen Walsh continues her dominance, lowering her own 100m butterfly world record yet again. In combat sports, Naoya Inoue successfully retained his undisputed super bantamweight title against Nakatani. On a lighter note, a massive crowd gathered at Copacabana beach for a free Shakira concert.\n*   **The Esoteric & Essential:** *Esoteric Ebb* is earning praise as a must-play for fans of complex, narrative-driven gaming.\n*   **Notable Mentions:** Austrian authorities have apprehended a suspect linked to a disturbing case of rat poison discovered in baby food. In travel, Taiwan’s leader, Lai, faced diplomatic hurdles with a delayed trip to Eswatini due to denied overflight clearance.\n*   **Consumer Savings:** For those looking to optimize their spending, May brings a wave of promotions across various sectors, including deals on Anker’s 2-in-1 USB-C cables, Aura digital photo frames, and various seasonal discount codes for services like TurboTax, Ulta, and Rover.','[{\"title\": \"Specsmaxxing \\u2013 On overcoming AI psychosis, and why I write specs in YAML\", \"url\": \"https://acai.sh/blog/specsmaxxing\"}, {\"title\": \"A Couple Million Lines of Haskell: Production Engineering at Mercury\", \"url\": \"https://blog.haskell.org/a-couple-million-lines-of-haskell/\"}, {\"title\": \"This Month in Ladybird - April 2026\", \"url\": \"https://ladybird.org/newsletter/2026-04-30/\"}, {\"title\": \"Dav2d\", \"url\": \"https://code.videolan.org/videolan/dav2d\"}, {\"title\": \"The IBM Granite 4.1 family of models\", \"url\": \"https://research.ibm.com/blog/granite-4-1-ai-foundation-models\"}, {\"title\": \"AI-generated actors and scripts are now ineligible for Oscars\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/02/ai-generated-actors-and-scripts-are-now-ineligible-for-oscars/\"}, {\"title\": \"Farewell, Jeeves: Ask.com shuts down\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/02/farewell-jeeves-ask-com-shuts-down/\"}, {\"title\": \"Netflix delays Greta Gerwig\\u2019s \\u2018Narnia\\u2019 movie for big theatrical push in 2027\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/02/netflix-delays-greta-gerwigs-narnia-movie-for-big-theatrical-push-in-2027/\"}, {\"title\": \"The best AI dictation apps, tested and ranked\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/02/the-best-ai-powered-dictation-apps-of-2025/\"}, {\"title\": \"Beyond Lovable and Mistral: 21 European startups to watch\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/02/beyond-lovable-and-mistral-21-european-startups-to-watch/\"}, {\"title\": \"Meta&#8217;s historic loss in court could cost a lot more than $375 million\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/policy/922380/new-mexico-meta-public-nuisance-trial-kids-safety\"}, {\"title\": \"Spirit Airlines shuts down after Trump\\u2019s war on Iran doubled jet fuel prices\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/business/922788/spirit-airlines-shutdown\"}, {\"title\": \"Aura\\u2019s delightful Aspen photo frame is on sale for $30 off this weekend\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/gadgets/922513/aura-aspen-carver-walden-digital-photo-frame-mothers-day-deal-sale\"}, {\"title\": \"Anker\\u2019s discounted 2-in-1 USB-C cable is a great way to spend $15\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/gadgets/922288/native-union-anker-2-in-1-usb-c-cable-mothers-day-sale-deal\"}, {\"title\": \"Playing Esoteric Ebb is like rolling the dice with a great DM\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/games/903575/esoteric-ebb-review-pc-steam\"}, {\"title\": \"Limited Time: TurboTax Full Service Coupons This May\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/turbotax-coupon/\"}, {\"title\": \"Ulta Promo C