light clearance - NPR\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMivwFBVV95cUxPZWQwU3c5TU05WkJwR2NrbV9MYVJlMmI0QnkwYzdoTWh5bjZOd25zVDhkaXFGcDlXeWZfYkpPNEplX2ZQWFFTSk9OVXRsSEMxd20xQk9FZGFSdmlvV3lnVkd5Z1ZtS1AweWpPQzRkNkhOSXpXZ3IzM2FzMnlyRXRJeWdid3F4WjRhSjM1bDFqV2tzUVpfVTl0MG9LeE9mOUMyYnN4TXlKb3ZFcUdFeDVmRHJqUThiOXRnOG9oemQ4UQ?oc=5\"}]','2026-05-03 09:00:47'),(39,'Daily Planet - May 04, 2026','### Global Affairs: Tensions at the Strait of Hormuz\nThe geopolitical spotlight remains fixed on the Strait of Hormuz, where the deepening oil crisis continues to exert severe pressure on the Asia-Pacific region. Japanese Prime Minister has characterized the situation as having an \"enormous impact,\" as ongoing volatility in the region reaches a critical junction. Amidst these tensions, Donald Trump has signaled that the United States will intervene to \"guide\" stranded vessels out of the Strait—a move explicitly rejected by Iran, which has warned the U.S. to refrain from involvement. In other developments, a seized Iranian ship’s crew has been repatriated to Pakistan.\n\nMeanwhile, the war in Ukraine has entered a complex phase; while Russian strikes continue to claim civilian lives and target energy infrastructure, some reports suggest that the broader conflict may be inadvertently creating conditions that strengthen Ukraine’s strategic position, potentially altering the landscape for future ceasefire negotiations. Domestically, former New York Mayor Rudy Giuliani is reported to be in critical condition, and a Secret Service agent has been wounded in the investigation surrounding the recent attack at the correspondents\' dinner.\n\n### Technology & Innovation: The Reality of the \"Boring\" AI Era\nThe tech sector is currently navigating the friction between rapid innovation and institutional integration. Industry leaders, such as Nicolas Sauvage, are increasingly shifting focus toward the \"boring\" applications of AI—prioritizing pragmatic, high-utility automation over mere novelty. \n\nThis maturation is reflected in recent findings from Harvard, which suggest AI is already capable of outperforming human doctors in emergency room diagnostic accuracy. However, this growth is not without conflict: the creator of the iconic \"This is fine\" meme has publicly accused an AI startup of intellectual property theft, highlighting the ongoing legal and ethical disputes regarding AI training data. In the software space, developers are leveraging new efficiencies, such as \"DeepClaude,\" to integrate DeepSeek’s capabilities into agentic coding workflows, while the niche world of hardware continues to evolve with advancements in humanoid robot actuators and high-bandwidth LoRa mesh networking.\n\n### Quick Hits\n*   **Aviation & Commerce:** Following the abrupt collapse of Spirit Airlines, a grassroots effort led by a TikToker is attempting to rally pledges for a private acquisition of the carrier.\n*   **Gaming & Culture:** Nintendo reportedly pushed back against Amazon regarding illegal demands, according to Reggie Fils-Aimé; meanwhile, the market for AI-generated music on streaming platforms continues to grow, leaving many to wonder if consumer demand actually exists.\n*   **Gear & Lifestyle:** \n    *   **Audio/Tech:** Shokz is offering a Mother’s Day promotion on their OpenRun Pro 2 headphones, and \"digital Polaroids\" using NFC and E-ink are emerging as a clever way to digitize home decor.\n    *   **Review:** The 2026 Asus Zenbook A16 earns praise for performance, provided one can overlook its lackluster aesthetic.\n    *   **Utility:** With travel season approaching, the debate over the best luggage trackers (AirTags vs. Pebblebee) and travel totes remains a top priority for the frequent flyer. \n*   **Public Safety:** Authorities are investigating a suspected virus outbreak on an Atlantic cruise ship that has resulted in three deaths, and a rare police operation saw an officer descend into a crocodile-infested river to recover human remains.','[{\"title\": \"Humanoid Robot Actuators\", \"url\": \"https://www.firgelli.com/pages/humanoid-robot-actuators\"}, {\"title\": \"Using \\u201cunderdrawings\\u201d for accurate text and numbers\", \"url\": \"https://samcollins.blog/underdrawings/\"}, {\"title\": \"BYOMesh \\u2013 New LoRa mesh radio offers 100x the bandwidth\", \"url\": \"https://partyon.xyz/@nullagent/116499715071759135\"}, {\"title\": \"DeepClaude \\u2013 Claude Code agent loop with DeepSeek V4 Pro\", \"url\": \"https://github.com/aattaran/deepclaude\"}, {\"title\": \"Texico: Learn the principles of programming without even touching a computer\", \"url\": \"https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/shows/texico/\"}, {\"title\": \"Nicolas Sauvage is betting on the boring parts of AI\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/04/nicolas-sauvage-is-betting-on-the-boring-parts-of-ai/\"}, {\"title\": \"We\\u2019ll take it: a TikToker rallies pledges to buy Spirit Airlines after its abrupt weekend collapse\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/03/well-take-it-a-tiktoker-rallies-pledges-to-buy-spirit-airlines-after-its-abrupt-weekend-collapse/\"}, {\"title\": \"\\u2018This is fine\\u2019 creator says AI startup stole his art\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/03/this-is-fine-creator-says-ai-startup-stole-his-art/\"}, {\"title\": \"In Harvard study, AI offered more accurate emergency room diagnoses than two human doctors\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/03/in-harvard-study-ai-offered-more-accurate-diagnoses-than-emergency-room-doctors/\"}, {\"title\": \"TechCrunch Mobility: How do you issue a ticket to a robotaxi?\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/03/techcrunch-mobility-how-do-you-issue-a-ticket-to-a-robotaxi/\"}, {\"title\": \"Reggie Fils-Aim\\u00e9 says Amazon once asked Nintendo to break the law\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/games/922840/reggie-fils-aime-amazon-nintendo-illegal\"}, {\"title\": \"Shokz\\u2019s bassy OpenRun Pro 2 are $40 off thanks to a new Mother\\u2019s Day promo\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/gadgets/922616/shokz-openrun-pro-2-bone-conduction-headphones-mothers-day-deal-sale\"}, {\"title\": \"These reusable digital Polaroids are a clever way to cover a fridge in memories\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/917067/vidabay-snap-nfc-e-ink-paper-fridge-magnet-photo-hands-on\"}, {\"title\": \"How the internet\\u2019s favorite squirrel dad made the hottest camera app of 2026\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/921690/dualshot-recorder-iphone-camera-app-derrick-downey-jr\"}, {\"title\": \"AI music is flooding streaming services \\u2014 but who wants it?\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/column/921599/ai-music-is-flooding-streaming-services-but-who-wants-it\"}, {\"title\": \"The Best Star Wars Gifts for Everyone, From Padawans to Jedi Masters (2026)\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/gallery/best-star-wars-gifts/\"}, {\"title\": \"Asus Zenbook A16 (2026) Review: Savor the Power, Ignore the Beige\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/review/asus-zenbook-a16-2026/\"}, {\"title\": \"15 Best Gifts for Plant Lovers and Gardeners (2026)\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/the-best-gifts-for-plant-lovers-and-gardeners/\"}, {\"title\": \"How to Track Your Luggage (2026): AirTag, Pebblebee, CaseSafe\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/story/how-to-track-your-luggage/\"}, {\"title\": \"Best Travel Tote Bags for Every Kind of Excursion (2026): Away, Le Pliage, Topo Designs\", \"url\": \"https://www.wired.com/gallery/best-travel-tote/\"}, {\"title\": \"The Iran war has strengthened Ukraine in surprising ways. Could a ceasefire with Russia be closer?\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cgjp7vpee03o?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Three dead in suspected virus outbreak on Atlantic cruise ship\", \"url\": \"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cy0294829ndo?at_medium=RSS&at_campaign=rss\"}, {\"title\": \"Russian strikes kill 10 as Zelensky says Ukrain