cting fight - The Washington Post\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMikwFBVV95cUxPRmF2ZmpUdkE2M1k1OVpJdVU3MUNmNkVPeXQyUExWanhrMWFUM2RNU3B4YTJjeDlFU3pmdVp3RW1vdnR2dVRrX1VHWk9saTV3SHdEekZOWlh4ZGtGbTV6RnMyZ0FyVlJkQ1RBSm0ydXl2djNjM1JUU1lUYUJJZ0pzWG81MFRrX1BtTkxlMVhCOHlQek0?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Man wounded after allegedly shooting at Secret Service near White House, bystander struck - WTOP\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMimgFBVV95cUxPM1lPRDlUU1dsRU5OZWlzWTZyTkhycHp5UHh6Q2JhZFU5MlA3R1hiYnIzeGEzUmc4NTN0Q3NjRzlLdm5WdXotbnQtMzlQZ012R2xLdWNYb3Z4d0RLWHBKMWlONlNPbkdIclNseWFLejl4RjhRX2xmRWx1MnNmcUR0RWExN05TMVhycXZwOFl4WklhQU42VVJSZHBB?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"\\u2018Dangerous escalation\\u2019: World condemns Iran after attacks on UAE - Al Jazeera\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"AP, Washington Post, Reuters and Minnesota Star Tribune among Pulitzer winners for 2025 work - Politico\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.?oc=5\"}]','2026-05-05 09:00:41'),(41,'Daily Planet - May 06, 2026','### Global Affairs: Geopolitical Tension and Domestic Shifts\n\nThe geopolitical landscape remains precarious, with the standoff in the Strait of Hormuz increasingly threatening to devolve into full-scale conflict. As the US considers its options—having paused \"Project Freedom\" amid President Trump’s search for a diplomatic off-ramp—the resulting friction is beginning to strain the transatlantic alliance, specifically widening the rift between Washington and Berlin. \n\nIn the Middle East, the humanitarian toll of ongoing hostilities is mounting. BBC reports detail the devastating impact of a recent ten-minute Israeli bombardment in Lebanon, while an tragic shopping centre fire in Iran has claimed at least eight lives. Simultaneously, Syrian authorities report the disruption of a Hezbollah-linked cell engaged in assassination plots, further underscoring the regional volatility. Elsewhere, humanitarian crises persist in Ukraine, where civilians remain trapped in frontline cities along perilous routes.\n\nOn the domestic political front, the 2026 election cycle is intensifying. Vivek Ramaswamy has secured the Republican nomination for the Ohio gubernatorial race, while the political fallout from President Trump’s influence continues to shape GOP primaries, most notably in Indiana. Meanwhile, in California, candidates for governor are clashing over the state’s most pressing dilemmas: housing and immigration. \n\n### Technology & Innovation: The Limits of AI Hype\n\nThe tech industry is currently navigating a period of recalibration, balancing aggressive investment with the realities of consumer adoption. SAP has made a significant $1.16 billion bet on a nascent German AI lab, signaling continued institutional confidence in the sector. However, the narrative is not uniformly bullish. Microsoft has officially abandoned its \"Xbox Copilot\" AI project, and Bumble is currently facing a decline in paying users as it prepares for a substantial platform overhaul.\n\nConsumer tech is also seeing a shift toward deeper integration and accountability. Apple is navigating a $250 million settlement over failed promises regarding Siri’s intelligence, even as reports suggest iOS 27 may finally allow users to select their preferred third-party AI models. In the smart home space, Google is enhancing Gemini’s capabilities to manage more complex home automation requests, while researchers at Georgia Tech have introduced smart sensors that operate without traditional battery requirements—a potentially significant leap for sustainable IoT.\n\n### Quick Hits\n\n*   **Corporate & Digital:** Cloudflare now enables autonomous agents to purchase domains and deploy infrastructure directly. In social media, Meta’s Threads is finally introducing direct messaging on the web.\n*   **Infrastructure:** A significant DNSSEC disruption recently impacted .de domains, though the issue has since been resolved.\n*   **Logistics & Robotics:** Nuro has secured a driverless testing permit, positioning itself ahead of the upcoming Uber robotaxi launch. Meanwhile, DIY innovation continues to flourish, exemplified by the development of \"CARA 2.0,\" a refined take on the open-source robot dog.\n*   **Culture & Sport:** The Oklahoma City Thunder secured a decisive Game 1 victory over LeBron James and the Los Angeles Lakers. In North Korea, the carefully curated public appearances of Kim Ju Ae remain a focal point for intelligence analysts seeking to decode succession planning.\n*   **Consumer Savings:** A variety of promotional offers are active for May 2026, including discounts for The Motley Fool, 1Password, Bose, Hydrow, and AirDoctor.','[{\"title\": \"Agents can now create Cloudflare accounts, buy domains, and deploy\", \"url\": \"https://blog.cloudflare.com/agents-stripe-projects/\"}, {\"title\": \"StarFighter 16-Inch\", \"url\": \"https://us.starlabs.systems/pages/starfighter\"}, {\"title\": \"CARA 2.0 \\u2013 \\u201cI Built a Better Robot Dog\\u201d\", \"url\": \"https://www.aaedmusa.com/projects/cara2\"}, {\"title\": \"DNSSEC disruption affecting .de domains \\u2013 Resolved\", \"url\": \"https://status.denic.de/pages/incident/592577eab611ce1e0d00046f/69fa60ef9d12f5057a974f38\"}, {\"title\": \"Batteries Not Included, or Required, for These Smart Home Sensors\", \"url\": \"https://coe.gatech.edu/news/2026/04/batteries-not-included-or-required-these-smart-home-sensors\"}, {\"title\": \"Peter Sarlin\\u2019s QuTwo reaches $380M valuation in angel round\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/05/peter-sarlins-qutwo-reaches-380m-valuation-in-angel-round/\"}, {\"title\": \"Marc Lore says that AI will soon enable anyone open a restaurant\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/05/marc-lore-says-that-ai-will-soon-enable-anyone-open-a-restaurant/\"}, {\"title\": \"Nuro receives driverless testing permit ahead of Uber robotaxi service launch\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/05/nuro-re