\"title\": \"Harvard Canvas Site Goes Down After University Listed in Instructure Breach | News - The Harvard Crimson\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMicEFVX3lxTE43U2JmT2RaOUNsWkdpOVFxaTlXQ3l5Y0ppajByOEJ1VnN6ei1oMExNZVJSZzlvbWxJbE5FQUlnMklsZTJndlU3UFF2a0lqQ3JrN0hvSndrNlhKZExvUUYyR2YtSXZqakd5emlZYmM4UXc?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"CENTCOM Protects U.S. Warships Transiting Strait of Hormuz > U.S. Central Command > Press Release View - centcom.mil\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"DeSantis acknowledges Florida\\u2019s \\u2018Alligator Alcatraz\\u2019 may wind down operations - Politico\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMimgFBVV95cUxPYm9VXzM0bHhrTk16cXRGMmdRYmIxTThKWWdhZFM4T0NUS1NIYkVwNE4xZ0lYRFpsemZ6YjVfc3VpeC1RN0U3akFZb0N4OEc0UkVPVllldG9nVmJtM3lPT3BIVEdJM0hkYWdIaWo3aWVEU3NtM0s1QXFLaHpWTFhnWW5taWpISHplbTlMSFZILXU0MV9FQmVCS1pn?oc=5\"}]','2026-05-08 09:01:02'),(44,'Daily Planet - May 09, 2026','### Global Affairs: Geopolitical Friction and Public Health\nTensions in the Middle East have escalated, as the U.S. confirmed it engaged two Iranian-flagged tankers, while Tehran condemned the act as a \"reckless military adventure.\" Simultaneously, volatile conditions persist in the West Bank, where reported settler violence has involved the burning of homes and vehicles. \n\nIn Eastern Europe, Russia marked a scaled-back Victory Day, serving as a backdrop for Vladimir Putin’s continued denunciations of NATO. Amidst these shifting alliances, a diplomatic development emerged as Donald Trump claimed that Russia and Ukraine have agreed to a three-day ceasefire and a prisoner exchange—a claim that warrants close observation as the situation unfolds.\n\nOn the health front, the Canary Islands are currently on high alert, bracing for the arrival of a cruise ship currently grappling with an outbreak of the hantavirus. Meanwhile, Yemen’s military remains in a precarious state, with financial instability leading to stalled wage payments for soldiers. Closer to home, a significant domestic legal hurdle arose as the Virginia Supreme Court struck down a gerrymandered redistricting plan, signaling potential shifts in the state’s electoral landscape. Finally, the Pentagon has declassified decades of UFO files, offering the public a peek into documented encounters with unidentified hovering objects and anomalous light phenomena.\n\n### Tech & Innovation: The AI Paradox and Corporate Shifts\nThe tech sector is currently navigating an uncomfortable dissonance between record-breaking performance and widespread labor disruption. Cloudflare reported record revenue this quarter, yet simultaneously confirmed that AI implementation has rendered 1,100 roles obsolete. This trend of automation continues to dominate discourse, further highlighted by debates surrounding the massive energy requirements of AI data centers and the ongoing scrutiny of how AI models are deployed, as evidenced by a court ruling against DOGE for illegal and ill-advised use of ChatGPT.\n\nIn the streaming wars, Amazon’s Prime Video is pivoting toward the engagement-heavy \"Clips\" model, joining Netflix and Disney in implementing a vertical video feed. This comes as users report ongoing issues with Google’s reCAPTCHA implementation on de-googled Android devices, and developers continue to explore the \"unreasonable effectiveness\" of foundational tools like Claude Code and the timeless, if often ignored, lessons of *The Mythical Man-Month*.\n\n### Quick Hits\n*   **Corporate Moves:** Laid-off Oracle workers failed in their attempts to negotiate improved severance terms.\n*   **Hardware:** Asus is taking a page from the Elgato playbook with a new secondary touchscreen display, while Logitech continues to offer seasonal discounts. \n*   **Consumer Tech:** Yarbo has issued a formal promise to address security concerns following an incident involving one of its autonomous lawn mowers.\n*   **Media Policy:** The FCC’s recent warnings regarding political interviews are being challenged by ABC, which argues the directives exert a \"chilling\" effect on First Amendment protections.\n*   **NBA Playoffs:** Victor Wembanyama’s commanding performance propelled the Spurs past the T-Wolves, while the Knicks secured a victory over the Sixers.\n*   **Market Trends:** San Francisco’s real estate market continues to defy conventional logic, showing signs of severe volatility.\n*   **Savings:** A variety of promotional offers are currently available for services including Instacart, HelloFresh, Blue Apron, and T-Mobile.','[{\"title\": \"A recent experience with ChatGPT 5.5 Pro\", \"url\": \"https://gowers.wordpress.com/2026/05/08/a-recent-experience-with-chatgpt-5-5-pro/\"}, {\"title\": \"Google broke reCAPTCHA for de-googled Android users\", \"url\": \"https://reclaimthenet.org/google-broke-recaptcha-for-de-googled-android-users\"}, {\"title\": \"Using Claude Code: The unreasonable effectiveness of HTML\", \"url\": \"https://twitter.com/trq212/status/2052809885763747935\"}, {\"title\": \"Mythical Man Month\", \"url\": \"https://martinfowler.com/bliki/MythicalManMonth.html\"}, {\"title\": \"OpenAI\\u2019s WebRTC problem\", \"url\": \"https://moq.dev/blog/webrtc-is-the-problem/\"}, {\"title\": \"Laid-off Oracle workers tried to negotiate better severance. Oracle said no.\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/08/laid-off-oracle-workers-tried-to-negotiate-better-severance-oracle-said-no/\"}, {\"title\": \"San Francisco\\u2019s housing market has lost its mind\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/08/san-franciscos-housing-market-has-lost-its-mind/\"}, {\"title\": \"Prime Video follows Netflix and Disney by adding a TikTok-like \\u2018Clips\\u2019 feed in its app\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/08/prime-video-follows-netflix-and-disney-by-adding-a-tiktok-like-clips-feed-in-its-app/\"}, {\"title\": \"Intel\\u2019s comeback story is even wilder than it seems\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.