e. Meanwhile, in London, domestic pressure on Prime Minister Keir Starmer has reached a boiling point, with mounting calls from within his own party for his resignation. Simultaneously, France is attempting to pivot away from its colonial legacy, with President Macron announcing a substantial $27 billion investment in Africa during a summit in Kenya, signaling a strategic bid to reshape relations with the continent.\n\nTragically, stability remains elusive elsewhere. In Pakistan, a fuel crisis continues to cripple daily life, while tensions have spiked following a military strike on a rehabilitation center that resulted in 269 Afghan fatalities. Closer to home, a shooting incident near Harvard University has served as a grim reminder of domestic security challenges.\n\n### Tech & Innovation: The AI Industrial Evolution\n\nThe tech sector is currently grappling with the dual realities of rapid AI integration and the necessity of robust security. \n\n*   **The AI Pivot:** The ripple effects of AI adoption are increasingly tangible in the labor market. General Motors has initiated a significant layoff of hundreds of IT staff, explicitly pivoting to recruit talent with specialized AI skill sets. In the venture space, Robinhood is reportedly preparing for a second retail-focused IPO to capitalize on the ongoing AI market rally, while defense technology firm Helsing is set to raise $1.2 billion at an $18 billion valuation. \n*   **Intelligence & Interaction:** Innovation in AI continues to evolve beyond mere generation; Mira Murati’s new venture, \"Thinking Machines,\" is focused on developing systems that prioritize active listening and natural interaction, aiming to bridge the gap between human conversation and machine processing. OpenAI has also moved to solidify its competitive stance with the release of *Daybreak*, its security-focused response to Claude Mythos.\n*   **Security & Infrastructure:** The industry is reckoning with supply-chain vulnerabilities, exemplified by the TanStack postmortem regarding a recent NPM compromise. Meanwhile, progress continues on the consumer front as cross-platform messaging between Android and iPhone finally achieves full end-to-end encryption—a long-awaited victory for digital privacy.\n\n### Quick Hits: Notable Mentions\n\n*   **Medical Breakthrough:** UCLA researchers have identified a landmark stroke rehabilitation drug capable of actively repairing brain damage, a potential turning point for neurological recovery.\n*   **Hardware & Gadgets:** Sony has refined its personal wearable air conditioner (Reon Pocket Pro Plus) for better ergonomics. On a more whimsical note, a new adblocker inspired by the 1988 film *They Live* offers a unique, albeit cynical, take on modern digital advertising.\n*   **Robot Accountability:** In a rare victory for consumer rights, the robot lawn mower company Yarbo has committed to removing an intentional backdoor from its software.\n*   **Oddities & Bureaucracy:** A non-profit is currently suing the federal government to block plans to paint the iconic Lincoln Memorial Reflecting Pool blue.\n*   **Consumer Savings:** For those navigating the current economic landscape, significant discounts are currently available via various promo codes for Chewy, Dell, Booking.com, Canon, and Paramount+.','[{\"title\": \"Postmortem: TanStack NPM supply-chain compromise\", \"url\": \"https://tanstack.com/blog/npm-supply-chain-compromise-postmortem\"}, {\"title\": \"Screenshots of Old Desktop OSes\", \"url\": \"http://www.typewritten.org/Media/\"}, {\"title\": \"They Live (1988) inspired Adblocker\", \"url\": \"https://github.com/davmlaw/they_live_adblocker\"}, {\"title\": \"If AI writes your code, why use Python?\", \"url\": \"https://medium.com/@NMitchem/if-ai-writes-your-code-why-use-python-bf8c4ba1a055\"}, {\"title\": \"UCLA discovers first stroke rehabilitation drug to repair brain damage (2025)\", \"url\": \"https://stemcell.ucla.edu/news/ucla-discovers-first-stroke-rehabilitation-drug-repair-brain-damage\"}, {\"title\": \"Thinking Machines wants to build an AI that actually listens while it talks\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/11/thinking-machines-wants-to-build-an-ai-that-actually-listens-while-it-talks/\"}, {\"title\": \"Riding an AI rally, Robinhood preps second retail venture IPO\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/11/riding-an-ai-rally-robinhood-preps-second-retail-venture-ipo/\"}, {\"title\": \"GM just laid off hundreds of IT workers to hire those with stronger AI skills\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/11/gm-just-laid-off-hundreds-of-it-workers-to-hire-those-with-stronger-ai-skills/\"}, {\"title\": \"Finally, texts between Android and iPhone users can be end-to-end encrypted\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/11/finally-texts-between-android-and-iphone-users-can-be-end-to-end-encrypted/\"}, {\"title\": \"Daniel Ek-backed defense tech Helsing to raise $1.2B at $18B valuation\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/11/daniel-ek-backed-defense-tech-helsing-to-raise-1-2b-at-18b-valuation/\"}, {\"title\": \"Sony upgraded its wearable AC so it\\u2019s cooler and better at hugging your neck\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/928220/sony-reon-pocket-pro-plus-personal-wearable-air-conditioner\"}, {\"title\": \"OpenAI just released its answer to Claude Mythos\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/ai-artificial-intelligence/928342/openai-daybreak-security-ai\"}, {\"title\": \"Yarbo says it will remove the intentional backdoor from its robot lawn mower\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/928289/yarbo-remove-robot-lawn-mower-backdoor\"}, {\"title\": \"Here&#8217;s what Mira Murati&#8217;s AI company is up to\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/ai-artificial-intelligence/928309/mira-murati-thinking-machines-ai-interaction-model\"}, {\"title\": \"Govee\\u2019s new portable smart lamp is on sale for the first time\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/gadgets/928249/gove