clgwRQ?oc=5\"}, {\"title\": \"Nonprofit sues the federal government over plans to paint Lincoln Memorial Reflecting Pool blue - NPR\", \"url\": \"https://news.google.?oc=5\"}]','2026-05-12 09:00:54'),(48,'Daily Planet - May 13, 2026','### The Global Ledger: May 13, 2026\n\n#### Geopolitical Tensions & The Global Stage\nThe diplomatic spotlight is firmly fixed on Beijing this week, as Donald Trump arrives for a high-stakes summit with President Xi Jinping. With the ongoing conflict in Iran—now in its 75th day—and mounting regional anxiety in the Gulf, the agenda is expected to be dominated by the status of Taiwan and the threat of escalating trade tariffs. Meanwhile, U.S. intelligence reports confirm that despite months of regional instability, Iran retains substantial missile capabilities, complicating the geopolitical calculus.\n\nIn other global developments, the political landscape remains volatile. In the UK, Prime Minister Keir Starmer has initiated crisis meetings with political rival Wes Streeting, reaffirming his pledge to remain in power despite internal pressures. In Africa, Ghana is initiating an evacuation of 300 citizens from South Africa following a wave of anti-immigrant protests, highlighting the fragility of regional stability. Meanwhile, a decade after his initial rise, Trump returns to a diplomatic arena facing a far more assertive and strategically entrenched China.\n\n#### Tech Innovation & The Digital Frontier\nThe intersection of artificial intelligence and public policy is deepening. TechCrunch notes that Medicare’s new payment model is essentially built for an AI-integrated healthcare system—a reality that has largely escaped the notice of the broader tech industry. In the legal sphere, the OpenAI-Elon Musk trial continues; testimony has revealed that Musk once considered handing control of the startup to his children, a detail that emerges as Sam Altman continues to defend the firm\'s trajectory on the stand.\n\nElsewhere, the security of digital infrastructure in Europe is under scrutiny. A recent audit has exposed significant vulnerabilities, identifying 3,000 tracking sites and 1,000 exposed `phpMyAdmin` instances, with an alarming 99% of government email communications lacking proper encryption.\n\nIn hardware and industry shifts:\n*   **Mobile:** Sony is attempting a comeback with an overdue design overhaul for its new Xperia phone. Meanwhile, Amazon’s Panos Panay has begun addressing persistent rumors regarding a potential new Fire phone.\n*   **Venture Capital:** Kevin Hartz’s A* has closed its third fund with a significant $450 million.\n*   **Startups:** Former Tesla executive Drew Baglino is pivoting to climate tech, launching a new heat pump startup.\n\n#### Quick Hits\n*   **Culture & Sports:** The sports world is in mourning following the death of Jason Collins, the NBA’s first openly gay player, at age 47. On the pitch, Lionel Messi has doubled his base salary at Inter Miami to $28 million annually, while Victor Wembanyama’s return spurred the Spurs to a 3-2 series lead in the NBA playoffs.\n*   **Infrastructure:** NASA’s Curiosity rover successfully resolved a mechanical setback, freeing its drill after it became snagged on a Martian rock.\n*   **Aviation:** The crisis within Air India continues to intensify as the industry awaits the final investigative report on the Ahmedabad crash.\n*   **Domestic U.S.:** Political intrigue in Nebraska has seen the Democratic nominee for Senate signal a potential withdrawal to support independent candidate Dan Osborn.\n*   **Consumer Alerts:** A variety of seasonal discounts are currently available, including savings on Corsair gaming gear, Valvoline services, Naturepedic products, and LG appliances.','[{\"title\": \"European governments: 3.000 tracking sites, 1.000 phpMyAdmins, and 99% poorly\", \"url\": \"https://internetcleanup.foundation/2026/05/european-governments-3000-tracking-sites-1000-phpmyadmins-and-99pct-poorly-encrypted-email-introducing-securitybaseline-eu/\"}, {\"title\": \"Deterministic Fully-Static Whole-Binary Translation Without Heuristics\", \"url\": \"https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.08419\"}, {\"title\": \"Restore full BambuNetwork support for Bambu Lab printers\", \"url\": \"https://github.com/FULU-Foundation/OrcaSlicer-bambulab\"}, {\"title\": \"The vi family\", \"url\": \"https://lpar.ATH0.com/posts/2026/05/the-vi-family/\"}, {\"title\": \"Googlebook\", \"url\": \"https://googlebook.google/\"}, {\"title\": \"Medicare\\u2019s new payment model is built for AI, and most of the tech world has no idea\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/12/medicares-new-payment-model-is-built-for-ai-and-most-of-the-tech-world-has-no-idea/\"}, {\"title\": \"Kevin Hartz\\u2019s A* just closed its third fund with $450M\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/12/kevin-hartzs-a-just-closed-its-third-fund-with-450-million/\"}, {\"title\": \"Former Tesla exec and Heron Power CEO Drew Baglino has founded a heat pump startup\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/12/former-tesla-exec-and-heron-power-ceo-drew-baglino-has-founded-a-heat-pump-startup/\"}, {\"title\": \"Musk mulled handing OpenAI to his children, Altman testifies\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/12/musk-mulled-handing-openai-to-his-children-altman-testifies/\"}, {\"title\": \"Anthropic warns investors against secondary platforms offering access to its shares\", \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/12/anthropic-warns-investors-against-secondary-platforms-offering-access-to-its-shares/\"}, {\"title\": \"Amazon&#8217;s Panos Panay addresses new Fire phone rumors\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/929412/amazon-panos-panay-interview-phone-transformer\"}, {\"title\": \"Sony\\u2019s new Xperia phone gets an overdue redesign\", \"url\": \"https://www.theverge.com/tech/927928/sony-xperia-viii-release-date-price-specs\"}, {\"title\": \"Sam Altman was winning on the stand, but it might not be enough\", \"url\": \"https://ww